column6: Taliah Waajid Curls, Waves and Naturals Curly Curl Cream, 6 Ounce
column14: I love this stuff! I have a 2b-3a curl pattern in my hair and feared this would be too heavy for me! I follow the Curly Girl method and forgot some of my hair products when traveling, and I'm very sensitive to coconut products and some proteins. Since this didn't have any obvious offenders and I don't have a degree in cosmetic chemistry, I gave it a try. Boy was I happily surprised! My hair looked great! My waves were definitely reaching their potential with this product. The smell is like a fruity shampoo, very pleasant. My curls were so incredibly soft and defined but still lasted all day without drooping. I normally would use a leave-in, a curl enhancer and a gel. But this time I used only this product and a light gel and my curls were lovely and frizz free. I have since tried it with a firmer hold gel on top but didn't like the texture/look of my hair nearly as much. I found it at CVS for $8.49 and it will continue to be a staple in my hair regimen!

[[VIDEOID:62a49e6ffdfc0602e4c2a396f85c621c]] This review is for the Apalus Glass Essential Oil Diffuser, Aromatherapy Diffuser, Ultrasonic Humidifier Air Purifier, with 7 Color LED Light.

This is a beautiful, high quality, THICK glass diffuser. The top cover which is the only glass part slides on and off to get to the water tank and essential oil basin. The glass is semi-transparent and provides a beautiful ambient glow once the light function is turned on.

The diffuser works well and produces a lot of humidified water into the surrounding air. It picks up the added oil in the water tank and disperses it effective. The two buttons on the front have a few settings. The left one clicks on to display the multicolor rainbow lighting. If you find a color shade you light in the rainbow spectrum, tap the button again and freeze the color for solid display. Once you are done with the light - turn it off by tapping a 3rd time.

The second button taps once for continuous 3 hour humidifying. If you want 30 seconds on and 30 seconds off, tap it again (great for essential oil). Once the 3 hours is up - or the tank runs dry (it has auto shut off protection), the unit shuts down ready for the next time you use it.

This diffuser plugs in the wall power and takes little power. Two of my wishes for this diffuser are an included measuring cup for filling the water tank with the correct amount, and an auditory beep when you press the front two buttons (currently no sound). Maybe subsequent versions will feature my wishes.

Overall, an EXCELLENT, beautiful diffuser for my oil collection. 5/5 stars for design, craftsmanship and materials.

If you have any questions please post below and I would be happy to answer! I received a free promotional sample of this item for my honest and unbiased review.

column7: My son has suffered from eczema mostly on his legs for some years. I have tried almost everything to soothe him and frequently use homemade concoctions. I was please to be able to try this shampoo and body wash in exchange for my honest review. First, my son in currently in a bit of a flare due to changing conditions, vacationing and swimming. I have been using this soap on him for a week. Normally he can't tolerate much more than an oatmeal bath but this is gentle enough to wash him without irritating his skin. I don't find that it is "healed" but but it certainly does a great job of mildly cleansing and his skin is not as itchy. I had to follow up with his medication and crave and it is looking better. I love the bottle and ease of dispensing.

column6: Schmidt's Natural Deodorant
column13: Switching to this product from here on out
column14:
Love this stuff! Impulse purchase on Prime day.

Want to remove chemicals from my diet and hygiene purchases, so I bought this. I love the smell - strong lime and just enough bergamot to remind me of Earl Grey tea. Application is a little weird, I don't know why they couldn't package it in a slender tube or like a typical click stick. I don't rub it between my hands; I use the little applicator to stripe it across my underarm, then I rub my arms back and forth in a rowing motion to even and warm it into the skin.

Lasts about 12 hours in lightly sweaty conditions. So far has held up at outdoor events in Louisiana heat (over 100 degrees). Probably not for people who are outside ALL day and heavily sporty. May not be great for intense sport activities lasting multiple hours, but works fine for a typical day including occasional heat, an hour walk and some light exercise.

column6: Remington Silk Ceramic Professional Hair Dryer
column14: My wife really loves this hair dryer, and she fell in love as soon as she took it out of the box. That's not surprising, since this blow dryer is pretty sleek looking. It's also got a cool finish, which the box calls a "Soft Touch Finish." Translation? It has kind of a matte, rubbery feel to it. The dryer's 1875 watts also produce some serious drying power, with two speeds and three heat settings. The bottom line? It dries hair super fast. One of the best features of this dryer is the removable air filter. It's simple to unscrew the filter on the back of the unit and clean out the accumulated hair and dust. It helps prevent that familiar burning hair smell from filling up the bathroom. My wife doesn't use the two included attachments--a diffuser and a concentrator--but it's nice to have them available. Add to that a rubber hang loop for easy storage and a FOUR-YEAR warranty, and you have yourself an impressive blow dryer!

column6: MelodySusie Long Curly Wig
column13: Beautiful wig well worth the price
column14: I was the maid of honor in my best friend's wedding this past weekend, and I really wanted an affordable wig that would look realistic enough to help me blend in with the rest of the bridal party (I recently shaved my head to support a friend going through chemotherapy). This wig was everything I could have asked for! Not only is it incredibly affordable, but it looked beautiful and realistic (definitely not overly-shiny or dull)! I actually received compliments on my hair from people who didn't realize I was wearing a wig (and from people who did). It is a very long wig (I am 5'3'' and it reached my waist) so I had to trim it a bit and it also gets tangled fairly easily, but both of these obstacles are easily overcome with proper maintenance. One critique I do have is that to me it looked more like a chocolate brown shade in person, not really a dark brown. However, maybe I just consider "dark brown" to be nearly black, which is what my natural hair color is. Even though the color was a little lighter than I thought, this wig is gorgeous and is definitely worth the price!

column14: When I first started to use this razor I noticed that the shave wasn’t all that great.  But as the weeks went by, it gradually started to do a better job.  I can accept that your body does adapt to a new razor, etc.  But yet even now, it doesn't do as good of a job as a simple razor blade would have done.  This razor comes with a cleaning system.  The cleaning system cleans the heads after each use and keeps the blades sharp for the next use - it also charges the razor at the same time while cleaning.  It also comes with an adjustable 5 setting trimmer, that works very well.  It has a travel case for the razor only.  This razor is for sensitive skin and I'm guessing that is maybe why it is so difficult to get a CLOSE shave, but as I would like a close shave and it not to leave stubble, I'm giving it a 4 star review - for the cost of this razor, I shouldn't have to complain that the shave is not Close enough.

column6: Hydraulic Barber Chair Styling Salon Work Station Chair Black New Omwah Brand
column13: If your cheap, this chair is for you.
column14: It works. It turns around and pumps up and down. I have been in hair design for 35 years and have been used to quality equipment. You do get what you pay for with this salon chair. I wanted the least expensive chair I could find. I believe I found it. I will only be standing on my feet behind the chair for a few more years. That is why I did not want to pay 500.00 plus for a hydraulic chair. The foot rest is wimpy and very difficult to install so it looks straight, but it works. The hydraulic pump is just okay. The chair doesn't seem to want to turn until you press your foot on the pump lever. I wasn't used to this, so it will take some time. The most disappointing aspect are the cushions. They're firm and assemble quite well but the stitching that creates the 6 square pattern is not lined up. This makes the chair look crooked, defective and cheap! At first glance, the chair in basic black isn't bad looking in a utilitarian sort of way. I only hope the chair will last until I retire. I bought two and one is not better or worse than the other. Update 9/2/15 Unfortunately I waited past the return window otherwise I would be returning these chairs. I have been using these chairs for just over a month. First there is some rust just starting on the chrome of the foot-rest. Second, the ability to turn the chair while a client is seated, is becoming harder and harder. Thirdly, the foot pump is crap. It is positioned way to high. I thought I would adjust to it but that has not happened. I end up having to look under the chair to locate it and then lift my foot. If you pump it all the way it seems to cancel your effort and not go up. You must only halfway pump it. This is so unlike any other chair I've ever worked on. Fourthly, the vinyl used is to soft and rubbery. It easily scratches from buttons, zippers, etc. Lastly, with the stitching on the seat being askew, and the footrest almost impossible to keep straight, the chair just looks awful. I can not recommend this chair.I am now giving it 1 star (they won't let me do 0) and will take the loss and find some new chairs.

column6: Panasonic Shaver & Epilator for Hair Removal
column13: less than middling capability at a high price
column14: I read many reviews before purchasing this epilator. They gave me the impression that this Panasonic ES-ED90 was a reliable quality product. Unfortunately, its performance is not living up to the praising reviews. Now I wonder how soon reviewers post their reviews after using this epilator. (I've been using mine for 7+ months.)  Before this, I owned a Braun epilator. Although it only came with one attachment, it out-performed the Panasonic in successfully gripping the hairs and pulling them out. Now, with this Panasonic, it takes me twice as long to remove the hairs on my legs and even fails to complete the job. In otherwords, some of the hairs that grow back are slightly ingrown and have left red dots on my legs. The attachment designed for underarms also takes a long time to fully remove the hairs. (On this same attachment is a flimsy metal grill guarding the skin against the grippers which bent a bit and popped out easily while I was gently cleaning it with the product brush.) The attachment designed for callus and rough skin removal works well and is comfortable to use. However, the shaving attachment nips at the skin a little and it's detachable bikini comb is too thick and coarse for the job.  For anyone who likes to hold the epilator near the top while epilating (for better control), be careful where you put your fingers. There is a button at the top for releasing the attachments. If you accidentally press this button while epilating, the head is likely to pop off.  Two more disappointments regarding this epilator: a) it takes a long while to charge for only an estimated 30 minutes of use, and b) it's unable to function when it's plugged into the wall (even after fully charging). The instruction booklet states that "the life of the (lithium ion) battery is 3 years if charged approximately once a week.....have the battery replaced by an authorized service center."  All in all, the Panasonic ES-ED90 is a mid to high maintenance product with only a few redeeming qualities.

column6: Oral-B Pro 7500 Power Rechargeable Electric Toothbrush Powered by Braun
column14:
There's not much to say that hasn't been covered by other reviews for this product but maybe some input from a long-time Sonicare user would be beneficial.

I have the Sonicare Diamond Clean and have used Sonicare for years. I like Sonicare and still use that toothbrush occasionally but I like this Black 7000 more and more each day. I feel like the clean is superior to the Sonicare.

As others have stated, the 7000 is a bit rougher on your teeth. If you have a very sensitive mouth, the Sonicare might be a better option; however, sometimes the Sonicare is so gentle that it doesn't remove that harder to clean debris- the 7000 doesn't have that problem. I love the Cross Clean and Floss Action brush heads- definitely my favorite 2.

Oral B has a much broader selection of brush heads when compared to Sonicare, which is something that I enjoy. It makes the brush more flexible. The Bluetooth "screen" for the 7000 is a gimmick. It doesn't do anything that a normal toothbrush timer couldn't do. I'd rather have the battery usage savings from removing bluetooth than have the "functionality" of this little display.

The battery life on the 7000 seems decent, though not as good as the Sonicare. The brush took almost 30 hours to charge out of the box- it was totally dead on arrival, so a dead to full charge is QUITE long. That being said, it seems to hold a charge well. I recently took the 7000 on a 4 day trip and used it twice a day on the Clean + setting, which is 3 minutes each time. So, over the course of the trip it was being used for 24+ minutes and it still had 2/3 battery bars lit. That seems to be about in line with the advertised battery life. Oral B claims 10 days of usage, 2 minutes twice a day, which equates to about 40 minutes of brushing over 10 days. I believe that is quite accurate, but still well below the Sonicare's 3 weeks of use on a charge.

Overall I think that the Oral B Black 7000 gives you the best and most thorough brushing experience available today, slightly edging out the Sonicare. That being said, the Sonicare wins in longevity, comes with a charging case, and charges MUCH faster.

If I had to pick between the Sonicare Diamond Clean and the Oral B Black 7000, I'd pick the Black 7000 but you can't go wrong with either.the best and most thorough brushing experience available today, slightly edging out the Sonicare. That being said, the Sonicare wins in longevity, comes with a charging case, and charges MUCH faster.

If I had to pick between the Sonicare Diamond Clean and the Oral B Black 7000, I'd pick the Black 7000 but you can't go wrong with either.

column14: So I have only used this about 4 times so far, so I don't have the best review, but I did a TON of research before deciding on this Dinair kit and here's the short version :) I was debating on 3 machines and ultimately picked this one from youtube tutorials and reviews. I am so glad I did!! I like that I can use other airbrush makeup in this machine (AKA Mac Pro Airbrush concealer) and the application is so flawless and light! I was a little nervous at first, it doesn't feel like you are wearing anything, but it actually covers very nice (I have a few age spots and dark circles, shhhhh!). I actually like the makeup that comes with it, but once it runs out I'll probably try other airbrush makeup in this machine. I have never done airbrush makeup before so I didn't want to invest a bunch of money into something I wasn't sure I would like. So far it's working like a dream! It comes with a few samples, but I use my own color corrector and highlighter. If you do use the airbrush highlighter- go Very EASY!!! Don't use the highlighter on the same speed as the foundation, or when you go outside you'll be competing with the sun for reflectiveness! The Dinair sprays evenly and I have had no issues with clogging or uneven spray so far! Had family try it out too & they seem to love it as well. The makeup seems to last all day, I am a heavy sweater-especially when I get stressed which is quite often. The makeup has stayed put all day, even through the hot summer days! (Although I do mist my finished face with e.l.f. makeup mist and set). I'll post later if I have any more info, but so far I am a happy purchaser!!

column6: Mother's Special Blend Skin Toning Oil, 8.5-Ounces (Pack of 2)
column14:
I didn't know this oil before but decided to give a try after reading a good review online. I use Mother's Special Blend All Natural Skin Toning Oil daily before going to bed since I was 5 and a half months pregnant. The oil is organic and a bottle lasts around 4 months (what a bargain, I use it all over from my bust to my hips and back). I don't love the smell (smells as vitamin E) and takes a few minutes to get absorbed (but a lot less than other oils I tried before). Right now I'm in my 35th week and haven't got any new stretch marks.
I must clarify that I've gotten excellent results (as for now, 0 new stretch marks, skin feels really smooth and stretchy). But as I said before, I only use this oil during the night and in the mornings I use Nicci Marie Stretch Mark Cream (as it gets absorbed really quickly). I started both on the same day so I'm not sure if I've could get the same results if I were using only one of them.
For me, the Mother's Special Blend All Natural Skin Toning Oil combined with the Nicci Marie Skincare it’s the perfect match. The cream can be a little bit pricey because (in my experience) it doesn't last a whole month, but I really think it’s worth the price.

My skin type: combo, acne-prone, 27 years old, hyper pigmentation from acne

My am routine is this:

-Wash face with water
-boots sensitive skin toner
-bha 2% on t-zone (apply w fingers and pat in)
- vitamin c serum
-Paula's choice clear mattifying spf 30 lotion

My Pm routine is this:
- ponds cold cream to take off makeup (w washcloth)
-Boscia face wash
-bha 2% on t-zone
-neutrogena on the spot acne treatment on forehead
-vitamin c serum
- jojoba oil

column13: The best you can get---even if others have a higher priced product.
column14:
Van Der Hagen Glycerin Shave Soap has the cleanest looking and cleanest smelling of any shave soap that I melt down in a double broiler in my shaving mug.
I have been using a double razor with (only "Feather New Hi-Stainless Platinum Coated Blades" from Japan - they give the sharpest and cleanest shave at 25 cents a blade, give or take.) and a 100% Badger Tail brush to lather.
I have been shaving this way for 5 years now - I find it the most economical way the shave now with very high priced blades on the market with 3 to 5 blades at about $5.00 per blade.
Invest in the best Badger Tail brush you can get, then buy your razor blades and soap in bulk.
You won't go wrong. It may take about a month until you master the razor blade, then you'll be done shaving in less that 5 minutes.
Be sure to cleanse your brush thoroughly and always hang it upside down to dry & your expensive brush will last you a life time.

column6: Waterpik ADA Accepted WP-660 Aquarius Water Flosser
column14:
I purchased the Waterpik WP-660 on the recommendation of my dental hygienist after she expressed some concerns with my gum health during my previous dental checkup. I've been using it about 3 times per week for the last 6 months and just returned from another check-up today. The hygienist and dentist both agreed that my gum health is substantially improved. I've also experienced fewer instances of bad breath since starting with the Waterpik.

As far as the unit itself, the quality is adequate considering the price. I would prefer to have about another 5 inches or so on the hose between the base and the nozzle, and I would prefer an option for a tip with a sharper angle. These minor criticisms are easily ignored when weighed against my improved dental health.

column6: Foot Rasp Callus File 2 Side Hard Dead Dry Skin Remover Pedicure
column14:
What I like about this foot file is that it has 2 different tools on it. On one side is the metal file (looks like a cheese grater) for tough calluses and on the other side is the black file (looks like sand paper or a giant nail file) which helps to smooth calluses. Both tools work alright, and I like that they are located on the same file as it is more convenient and saves space.

If you are looking for a manual foot file, I would recommend this handy 2-in-1 tool. I prefer using my electric foot file, as that does a better job in my opinion. But, this tool is nice to keep on hand in the shower when I want to do a quick file.

TIP: Order does matter! Use the metal file to file down calluses first, then use the black file to smooth the skin.

I received this product for free in exchange for sharing my honest and unbiased review. Opinion is entirely my own.

column6: Green Tidings All Natural Deodorant, Extra Strength All Day Protection; 2 Sizes; Unscented or Lavender (Vegan, Certified Cruelty Free)
column13: Effective in eliminating odor, but runs out fast and irritates skin.
column14: Okay, here's my comprehensive review of Green Tidings All Natural Deodorant after a solid two months of use; it works. The number one thing we're all looking for in a natural deodorant is effectiveness right? Well this is effective, hence the three stars. I'm not a particularly 'potent' guy, nor have I ever really struggled with body odor, so I cant say this will be as effective for everyone, but for me it did the trick and sustained the effectiveness for more than 24 hours. So why the two star deduction? One; the softness of the product means a lot goes on at one time (even when being conservative), and there's not much of it, so it goes super fast. The 1oz "tester" might last you a week, if you're lucky. The other star deduction is for a skin irritation factor that is prevalent during sustained use. I've had to alternate between another natural deodorant in order to let my underarm skin heal and normalize. Then when I alternate back to Green Tidings, the irritation (rash) returns. My wife experienced the same irritation.

column6: La Fresh Good Start Face Serum
column14:
I've been buying this elsewhere and was paying a small fortune for shipping so I am glad to have found it on Amazon. It is lightweight but moisturizing and has made my skin much smoother and it looks more plumped. So much so that my SO commented on it within a week of use. (!) I had used another, cheaper brand but my skin didn't improve and I think it may have become drier. Tried this and have stuck with it for a year. Now I won't buy anything else.

I use this twice a day after toner and before SPF moisturizer (day) or cream at night. Oh - make sure you use a good SPF while using this serum. It contains two potent forms of vitamin C and that can make your skin more susceptible to UV rays (and if not used correctly, can actually make your skin show signs of aging faster). One bottle lasts me 2 months so it works out to be about the same or a little less than most drugstore brands. There is no fragrance and my sensitive skin is never anything but happy with it and I think it is good for most skin types. Not too oily and not drying despite the vitamin C.

Definitely recommend for anti-aging, lightweight moisture and for smoother, softer skin. Totally worth the price!

column6: Bio-Oil Multiuse Skincare Oil
column14:
I've purchased Bio Oil multiple times and finally went for the 6.7 ounce bottle. I use it on my stretch marks from gaining weight. The stretch marks were "fresh" and it took my stomach to an angry red line mess to barely noticeable. Bio Oil does have a distinct smell, citrus-like, maybe an orange. It's okay, not a bad smell, but definitely noticeable. Bio Oil is a bit messy. It tends to leave oil marks on any surface the bottle comes in contact with. Which is fine, just wipe it up or do it in your bathroom. Quantity wise, I have never found myself going through Bio Oil at an alarming rate. The price is a bit high, but I'm expecting the 6.7 ounce to last me 2+ months, so worth it in my opinion. At the end of the bottle you can really stretch the use too.

Now, keep in mind. Stretch marks will never 100% go away, they are essentially scars. Bio Oil helped mostly with the coloration. You will still be able to see stretch marks even with Bio Oil. Personally, the stretch marks went from a red-purple to a shiny white (a whiter white then I am and I'm pale as can be). Bio Oil also thinned the stretch marks a bit. I call this successful. They will never fully disappear and do not believe anyone that tells you different (with the exception of drastic measures).

ps: I think the fact I was treating new scars might have helped make Bio Oil so successful.

The only product I would recommend for stretch marks, I hope it works for you like it did for me!

Next Up ~ The FOT. This stay's in my drawer in the bathroom. I don't use this one often, accept when applying beard oil/condition. I will sometimes decide to use this instead of my boar brush, but not often :) This comb gets the least amount of use.

Lastly ~ The R7T. Use this with Layrite Brown Tub Pomade. Absolutely LOVE this comb ... I start with the larger side, once tame, I switch to the finer side to clean areas up and give it a nice uniform look.

Like all Kent products, these are well made, and a necessity for any man in his daily arsenal. After 6+ months of daily use, I have yet to have a single tooth chip off, and I have got some thick/beastly hair (both on my face and scalp!)

column6: Surf's Up Ocean Soap with Organic Shea Butter 5oz
column14:
I don't mean to sound overenthusiastic but this is nice stuff. I've tried olive-based soaps before and been disappointed. I used to think that's why they were always so cheap at Ross, because people didn't like them. I didn't like the olive oil soap on my skin, it felt like a icky grime was on it.

So, trying this out, my husband and I both agree this is not that way at all. We got Sea Breeze, which is marketed for men but we both like it. It's a nice clean smell (not icky like Irish Spring) and is not strong at all. The scent is just right.

The bar itself looks good too, with the cream colored swirls in it. It doesn't come with the wood bar holder in the picture, so I used one I had got online too awhile back. It also is a big square so it didn't fit in my shower's tile soap shelf, but that's okay.

Two big things to note: this is not one of those soaps that are too soft and will only last a week or so: it is a firm soap and while it lathers well, it doesn't seem to shrink in half once you've used it.

The scent alone has me sold.

I rec'd a bar as a sample to inspect and review from manufacturer.

column14: I purchased this Vitamin C Cream because of the things it is good for. It says it's good for many things like exfoliating, producing collagen, reducing wrinkles, tightening and restoring skin, and many more. When I first received this product, I had gotten a really big box, leading me to believe something big was inside. When opening the box, I had found a really small container, which happened to be the vitamin C cream. It was really small to my liking, but I remained positive and decided to give it a try on my freshly washed face. When taking off the lid, I noticed that it had busted open, which could have been from the heat, but also made me feel a little nervous. I put a small amount on my hand and rubbed it on my face. I use a lot of exfoliating products and this really didn't feel like it exfoliated my face, seeing how it was basically a cream. After rubbing it in, I noticed my face felt really tight and dry. It went away after awhile, but I really didn't like the tightening feeling. I believe this product does what it claims, but I also believe everyone's skin reacts differently to different products.  *I purchased this product at a discounted price for my honest and unbiased review*

column6: Head & Shoulders Clinical Strength Dandruff and Seborrheic Dermatitis Shampoo 13.5 Fl Oz (Pack of 2)
column14:
I used the "no-poo" method for well over two years to clean my hair. I loved how natural it was, and how it helped my hair with not needing a wash every single day. Unfortunately, my scalp retaliated and I kept trying to use different natural methods to clear up the horrible dandruff. But no matter what I did, my scalp was itchy, scaly, and unbearable.
Finally, after all that time, I picked this up. I LOVE IT! I still only wash my hair every 5 or 6 days, but it doesn't get itchy and I no longer have any dandruff. It took about three or four washes for me to see about 80% clearance of the dandruff. But after the first wash, it was about 50% clear. A huge difference! It also kept my hair cleaner for longer.
This shampoo is fairly drying, but I rinse it well, use a good conditioner, and only wash every 5 or 6 days. I love this stuff and will recommend it to anyone I know with dandruff.

column14:
I LOVE these! I am fairly fair skinned, and like to have a light natural looking tan. I have always went to the tanning salon to achieve that look. As I have gotten older, the tanning salon becomes more of a concern. When I first heard about these, I immediately ordered them. I used one towel in the morning, and then again the same evening. It was very simple to use! By the next morning you could see a noticeable difference! The best part is it looked natural! No orange streaks! Now granted you have to be diligent about making sure you get every part of your body, and I always see a few spots I miss, but that is my fault. Honestly you can achieve that while in the sun as well! I always start with the towel still folded and apply one side to my face lightly, rubbing it in with my hand. Then I go to my legs, avoiding my feet, ankles and knees. Next my arms, avoiding the elbows. I do this while unfolding it the towel, so each side of the folded towel is used first. When completely unfolded I return to my face, making sure i apply it completely. Then go over my legs again, using a circular motion, this time going over my feet, ankles and knees. Then my arms, including elbows, and finish by going over the rest of my body.
This has worked perfect for me! I now only use these twice a week, which maintains my natural looking tan! It takes approximately 5 extra minutes in the morning to complete this! Totally worth it! Much healthier than the sun or tanning salon!

column6: Waterpik Ultra Cordless Plus Water Flosser WP450 1 ea
column14:
I was initially really happy with the product, as I am sure most people would be. It is certainly a convenient waterpick design. But I purchased the item at the start of 2014 and it is now August 2015 and the batter has died. This means I would have to buy a new waterpick every 1.5 years at this rate. My electric razor, by contrast, has a rechargeable battery that lasted many years already, so this seems to not have quite as good a battery.

The second problem I have is switched over to only using waterpick instead of flossing, because on the package it claims to be more effective than flossing. But I ended up getting lots and lots of cavities, more than I have ever had in my life, during the period I used this waterpick. I have since switched back to regular flossing. My dentist told me (after taking all of my money) that one should never just use a waterpick, but also use dental floss, because only dental floss can get under the gums.

If the company would be willing to refund or issue a warranty that might improve my review, but I could not figure out how to contact the seller.

column6: As I Am Curling Jelly
column14: I'm one of those people who sticks to the same products. I hate trying new products, because they never work for me. I was leery about trying this product, especially w/ the consistency.  I hate greasy, weighed down hair. I was looking for something to give my hair more definition for a longer period of time, but keep my hair soft at the same time. The products I used were great, but my hair would be super frizzy after only a couple days. So I reluctantly picked up this product to try.  I co-washed my hair then applied It's a 10 Leave In and Aussie Moist Conditioner as a styler. I put a light amount of curling jelly on top. I must say, I am so impressed with this product! It gives my hair a light hold, but adds so much definition. It's now Day 2, and my hair has never looked this good on Day 2. It's still very defined and not nearly as frizzy as it usually would be. I'm so happy I tried this product, especially since it's silicone and sulfate free. This will definitely be a staple product in my routine. The only con is the packaging. They should make this in a squeeze tube. The jar is just not user friendly and makes application more difficult than it needs to be. If they change the packaging, I would give it 5 stars.

column14:
Not long after after falling hopelessly in love with the excessive ritualism of shaving with a badger hair brush and straight edge, I started to notice a general trend of my overprotective sinuses starting to talk back, like when my mom me to summer camp with spf 400 sunscreen. I started conducting some tests, and found I got the same reaction when I shaved and when I used my roommate's German Shepherd for a pillow, and realized with a shock both that I would need to give up shaving for good and that I would,need to get a new pillow. That was a bad week.
But then came the synthetic shaving brush! "It won't be the same," I said, "how could I betray that old badger hair brush?" I said.

column14:
Pros:
- Great peppermint-vanilla scent
- Only scented candle I've found that is fine for people with chemical sensitivity
- Not overpoweringly strong
Cons:
- Not strong enough of a scent to fill a large room
- Candle is VERY small, only around 3-4 inches tall
- Doesn't burn for nearly as long as the 45 hour approximate advertised

In short, I can only recommend this candle for those who do have chemical sensitivities but are dying to have a scented candle around for the occasional burn. column6: 2 Set Best EXTRA LARGE Activated Charcoal Konjac Root Facial and Body Sponges - Purest Form of Vegan ALL Natural Beauty Products - Eco Friendly Hypoallergenic
column13: Love how gentle this facial sponge is!
column14:
Using the Shirataki Facial Sponge to cleanse and exfoliate my face is like being pampered at an expensive spa. The unique net-like structure of this sponge gently massages my skin while clearing away dead skin cells, clogged pores, and oils, reducing the size of my pores, balancing my skin pH, stimulating circulation, and leaves my skin feeling softer, smoother, and squeaky clean.

This Original Shirataki Facial Sponge is made entirely of the fibers of the Konjac plant, a renewable resource. It's all natural, eco friendly, biodegradable, cruelty free, and contains no additives whatsoever. This sponge came pre-moistened and ready to use right out of the bag. I like using my Shirataki sponge in the shower along with my favorite Vitamin C facial cleanser, and I gently massage my face for about 30 seconds or so, then rinse the sponge, squeeze it between my palms to remove the excess water, and hang it up by its string to a suction cup hook I keep in the shower stall. Keeping it in a well ventilated place will help it dry out and it should last about 3 months. Just be sure to let it get wet and expand again before the next time you want to use it

This is a high quality all natural sponge made of Konjac fiber that is extremely gentle on the skin yet very effective at exfoliating, unclogging pores, oxygenating and improving facial circulation, helping to clear up acne, and numerous other benefits. column6: Concha Nacar de Perlop Natural Bleach Cream #3 Original Formula Facial Care Products
column13: A Skincare Treasure; Slow and Steady for Clear Skin
column14:
First off, this cream is one of my treasured secret weapons.

This cream is a great treatment. I alternate between retinol and glycolic acid for my face and kojic acid for my body to even out my skin, treat minor blemishes and maintain my skin tone. I have a very high contrast look with dark hair so I fuss over the tiniest spots (I have very fair skin...think Dita von Teese fair). Both acids are very strong and the retinol can cause temporary red spots if applied to wrong areas of my face. That said, this cream is by far the most gentle of any exfoliation/lightening/evening/whitening method I've used. I love that I can read all the ingredient names!

Because it is so gentle, it does take a while to achieve the desired effect. This cream's main focus in on healing and subsequent maintenance of clear skin, so I would say about 3 weeks of consistent use and you will start noticing a difference. I use this mask daily after cleansing and stepping out of the shower at night. It does not take much to cover your whole face. I also mix pure pearl powder from my local Chinese herb store to enhance the process. It says to leave it on for up to an hour, but I've been known to stay on an hour and a half, sometimes 2 hours! The gentleness of this cream allows me to also use a light retinol after washing it off without adverse effects. Remember, since it does lighten the skin, the effects can only be preserved with the daily use of sunscreen during the day. With daily use and sunscreen, I noticed an exceptional difference at the 2.5 week mark. I haven't had one of those tiny persistent stress spots in the 4 months I've used this product.

For those people that are having breakouts, I agree with another reviewer that mentioned the initial skin purge. Some people's skin does that with almost all products. I've also heard of reactions to Irish moss as well as zinc oxide, especially since zinc oxide is the star in many mineral-based sunscreens. I recommend testing a patch of skin, about the size of your fingernail, for a week and observe the reaction. With this cream, slow and steady is the name of the game.d testing a patch of skin, about the size of your fingernail, for a week and observe the reaction. With this cream, slow and steady is the name of the game.

column6: Just For Men Original Formula Men's Hair Color, Ash Brown (Pack of 3)
column13: 20 years and counting. Still love it.
column14: I turned gray 20 years ago in my mid 30's and have been using this ever since.  I've tried others such as the similar Grecian Formula and various Clairol products, but always return to Just for Men.  The newest "non-drip" formula is the best yet as I don't end up with it all over my neck and forehead as in the old days of the more runny mix.  The color looks natural and people are always shocked on those very rare occasions when I do admit to coloring my hair. The key is not to go too dark. My original natural color was dark brown, but medium brown now looks perfectly natural on me in my mid 50s.  It helps to stay fit and take care of yourself to pull off the complete fraud!  I will be using JFM until it becomes downright silly for me to still have dark hair "at my age".  For now, I continue to be mistaken for a guy in his early/mid 40's and I like it.  I also like everything about this product from ease of use to end result.  The only thing I have ever had issue with is the "Up to six weeks" claim.  I am physically active and work up a sweat regularly.  I typically have to shower in the morning and again in the evening. A shower is not complete unless I wash my hair.  I can usually get only about three weeks before it starts to get the faded stale beer color rather than medium brown.  I refresh every 3 weeks before each haircut to avoid this. Good stuff.  Someone once told me that hair dyes may cause cancer.  I think that living one's life can cause cancer so I am not concerned.

column6: The Best Eyelash Growth Serum, Lash Conditioner, and Eyelash Enhancer – Grow Longer, Stronger Lashes in 30 Days – Our Beauty and Eyelash Growth Products Are 100% Guaranteed by Allura and Amazon (7 ml)
column13: Great, but takes time to get good results!
column14:
First off, it comes in this tube, kinda like what a liquid liner would come in. I have been using it consistently for about 2 weeks now and so far I am impressed with the results. Its not a miracle worker, however. It didn't grow my lashes overnight. Also, i think that i will get even better results as I keep using it. Its one of those products that you have to use for a while to actually see a difference.

One thing that i liked about it was that it actually has biotin in it, which is really good for growing your hair. I'm assuming its a good ingredient to use when trying to grow your lashes as well. Apparently its also supposed to prevent lash loss, which is great. It also has many other ingredients such as hyaluronic acid, vitamin e, and pro-vitamin B5. All of these put together is a great combo, i think!

The brush is kind of like a liquid eyeliner brush, so its very easy to apply. I didn't notice any sort of negative affects at all from this product. I know that some people have noticed those affects with other eyelash growing products, but i think this is supposed to be a much more gentle product.

So, all in all, i think this is a great product to use if you want to try growing your eyelashes a little. Its also really nice that you don't have to worry about it doing anything negative. You could also use it in your brows, which i haven't tried yet but i am going to soon! Just remember that this is going to take some time to work, and you need to use it daily for a while to see really good results.

He says the repairing treatment makes the difference in the steps for him. He can feel his skin is much better in texture with it on. He also drinks a lot of water with lemon and tries to steer clear of too much greasy, processed foods to deal with skin issues from the inside as well. If you have the typical kind of break outs and want to stay clear of internal medications and can stay true to how the product line is to be used, you should find success with this. column6: URPOWER 100ml 7 Color Changing Essential Oil Diffuser
column14:
An ultrasonic diffuser is a type of essential oil diffuser that disperses essential oils into the air. There are several different types of diffusers but this one is the very best and is easy to use. And if you are an essential oil lover, then you definitely want to own one! This diffuser has several different colors to choose from if you turn on the light function.

Diffusers work by breaking down the essential oil into micro molecules then projecting them into the air to fill a room or work space.
As the oils break down they release natural ozone and, freshen and improve the quality of the air! The particles remain in the air for several hours depending on how long the diffuser was on and how much oil was used.

This diffuser uses electronic frequencies to create vibrations that are carried to the surface where oils are floating. The vibrations vaporize the oil and disperse it into the air without using any kind of heat.

Essential oils benefits include that they can immediately penetrate the skin and cell membranes. They can actually diffuse throughout the blood and tissues instantly in a matter of seconds! Oils cross the brain-blood barrier and reach the amygdala and other limbic parts of the brain that control our mood, emotions and beliefs. So they can help us with our ability to handle stress, anger or any other emotion we are dealing with!

Essential oils soothe muscles and joints. They also can assist with minor aches and pains related to everyday activities especially in combination with massage. Yeah, who doesn't like a massage?

It's easy to clean, quiet and makes the house smell great! I received this unit at no cost to evaluate, test and review.

column14: I got this product for free from Bzzagent. I was thrilled to get the opportunity to try this whitening system, but felt that the actual results fell a little flat. Both tasted terrible and I just never felt like I ended up with really a really clean mouth. That being said, maybe that is not what this product is designed to do, but it is part of what I expected from a toothpaste. RESULTS.  I have used this product consistently for about three weeks now, and continue to use it in hopes that I see some good results, but so far the lesson that I have learned is that good result pictures are all about the lighting! I took my before photo the day the product arrived and my teeth looked surprisingly white in natural light. two weeks later after consistently using the product I photographed my smile in my bathroom and found that my teeth looked more stained that at the start. If I flipped the photos I'm sure I could convince people that I got a great result from this product, but that's not what I'm here for. Best of luck and I hope you end up with better results than I did.

column13: Very Good Overall, I Like And Recommend
column14: This moisturizing shampoo and conditioner smell really good, have a wonderful consistency to them, are healthy for your scalp, great for colored hair like mine, and really do replenish and moisturize giving you silky, shiny hair in the end. My only recommendation is that Loma offer a volumizing set as well because my already flat and volumeless hair remains exactly the same after using these. I still have to buy other products to give my hair lift and volume. The only other option is a daily shampoo and conditioner Loma makes which doesn't offer volume either. This is why I gave these only 4 out of 5 stars, but I still highly recommend them to anyone who wants a great smelling, healthy, and color-safe shampoo and conditioner. I bought these products because my hairdresser uses them at her salon, but I'm going to start shopping around again for a shampoo and conditioner that offers the same benefits AND volume as well. One last thing. the bottles themselves are skinner than in the picture as they are only 12 oz. bottles each which makes them kind of pricey then. I'm already low on conditioner than I am on shampoo and if you use a lot each time you wash your hair, then you might go through these fairly quickly than you'd like. Fortunately for me, I only wash my hair 2-3 times a week as recommended by my hairdresser so they've lasted a long time; I purchased them from Amazon in late March. Again, I still recommend these products as my hair is now healthier than it has ever been and if Loma ever offers a volumizing shampoo and conditioner, then I will go back to buying from them.

column6: Yes To Blueberries Softening Facial Exfoliator, 3.38 Ounce
column14:
I LOVE this stuff! I got it because I'm trying to boost my skin care routine and start fighting wrinkles early. Even if this stuff doesn't end up helping me prevent wrinkles, I'm happy I bought it.

I struggle with acne prone, extremely sensitive, easily scarring skin. I'm on antibiotics for my acne and although I haven't had a ton of break outs as of late, I've still been dealing with the leftover scars. When I first started using this stuff, I began breaking out. I assume it's because I have super sensitive skin and I've never really used an exfoliant before (GASP - I know...) After about a week, my skin got used to it. I also noticed after about 7-10 days, my acne scars had faded. I woke up one morning, and next thing I knew, CLEAR FACE. Don't get me wrong, if I look closely, I can still see a scar here or there, and some of the deeper ones are definitely still noticeable, but it's been a long time since I've been able to see myself with no make up and still consider my skin as looking to be on the clear/healthy side of things. If this stuff continues to fade my scars, I might just have to ditch my heavy foundations and powders!

The only con I have about this product is that it smells kinda funny. Aside from that, I highly recommend it. However, I'm not 100% sure that my great results are all due to this one product. Read below for details.

At the very same time I began using this exfoliant, I also began using a vegan alternate to petroleum jelly on my under eyes as a night cream, and a vitamin c hyaluronic serum and a daily moisturizer with sunscreen in it for the day. On top of that, as I said before, I'm on pills for my acne, as well as doctor prescribed Aczone for my mornings and Epiduo in the evenings. I've also been consistently using a Cerave cleanser in the mornings and a Cerave moisturizer as needed. I didn't start seeing results with my acne scarring until after using the exfoliant and hyaluronic serum. The pills, Aczone, Epiduo, and Cerave products mostly just combat my acne.

column13: my new favorite type of candle!
column14:
This is the first time I have ever tried a massage candle and I may never go back to regular candles. This massage candle is made of soy, so it burns cooler and cleaner than regular candles. Plus the fragrance is so much more long lasting. I was scared at first to dip my finger in the wax (because I have burned myself on hot wax more than once...ouch!), but since the soy burns cooler it was not hot. Once I tested the temperature I poured a little into my hand and rubbed the oil onto my arms. Wow! It felt so good. It was definitely more greasy than lotion but not as much as if it were plain oil (thicker than baby oil). It took awhile for it to sink in but it felt wonderful. I guess that is why it is good for massages (since it takes awhile to sink in). It was very moisturizing and my skin stayed soft all day. The fragrance lasted all day as well. I may have to look into all of the scents and find one that would work well for me to use instead of perfume on special occasions. This fragrance smelled really good, but I would not use it as my fragrance of choice. I was very impressed by this candle and would recommend it to anyone. This would make a great gift for someone that loves candles or for your special someone. I don't think my husband would mind smelling like THIS candle in exchange for a massage. :)

column6: Opalescence Go 15%
column13: Just starting my 10 day whitening adventure
column14:
After my whitening treatment at the dentist's office this morning failed (it was a uni-tray and the way my teeth sit, there was not enough coverage to whiten properly), I was given a box of these Go! 15% pre-loaded whitening trays as an alternative. I am using the first one now, and I do feel the burning sensation on my gums as others have mentioned, and some moderate random tooth pain (my teeth are sensitive). I like the outer-and-inner tray system they use; you pop the whole thing in your mouth and suck to get the inner tray to adhere, then toss out the outer tray. I used my fingers to smooth the inner tray on my teeth to make sure I get the maximum coverage (Warning! I think by doing this I may have discharged the whitening gel directly onto my gums which caused the burning and gum whitening).

I recently removed the first application and noticed some whitening of the gums that has persisted 30 minutes after removal of the product. Overall sensitivity has increased drastically, including one spot that was so sore I almost couldn't brush my teeth. I am hoping these immediate results are temporary!

Update after completing the whitening process:

My dentist noticed that my teeth had lightened up a bit (a shade or so he said), though I don't have any before/after pictures to share. The very first time I used the tray, as I said above, was very painful and I damaged my gums. I waited a few days before I used another tray. There was no pain or gum bleaching after the first application, no sore spots that hurt when I brushed my teeth after a couple days. I am getting a crown on a front tooth next week and want to ask if it's a good idea to keep a box of these trays and use one or two a year to maintain my current shade. Would use again for sure if I wasn't having dental work done so soon! Just be careful when you use it the first time and make very very sure you don't bleach your gums as well as your teeth!

column6: Merkur Heavy Duty Double Edge Razor (Blade Included)
column13: New to DE razors for neck and head shaving and will never look back!
column14:
I'm new into DE razors, so this is my first and only DE razor but it's hard to imagine what can be improved on.

It's got a great weight to it, a simple but elegant look and a perfectly knurled handle that's nice and grippy. Okay, one gripe is it doesn't do that cool butterfly open on top like I've seen some other razors do, instead the whole top just unscrews by twisting the bottom of the handle. Not as cool, but I don't feel like it's enough to dock it because now it doesn't have an ugly split down the center.

For me however this works great. I used to shave with cartridge razors every other day or every third day depending on how I felt. I like using this razor so much I shave every day now. Hell, if I have to take a second shower in a day before going out I'll use it twice in one day! Something about it is just fun, and the shave feels a million times better.

I do use this razor for my neck and head (no face, the beard will always be there), and while it takes a little getting used to in just a few weeks I've got the pattern down and can shave my neck in seconds and my head in a couple of minutes while getting a closer shave than cartridge ever allowed and without nicking myself (okay, well, the occasional nick, still).

Sadly, at least for me, the Merkur blades don't seem to be as well engineered as the handle itself. Sure, they work, but I have been using Personna blades to great satisfaction and am looking to try others as well when these run out.

All in all very pleased. I have always had a liking for things a bit more old school because, well, many older tools seem to provide with better results, albeit with more associated risk or effort involved. That is certainly true of DE razors, but your grooming ritual won't feel like you're playing with a toy, either. There are of course cost benefits that for me show up rather quickly: cartridge razors are expensive-- a pack of 15 costs around as much as this razor itself does. For a fellow that shaves his head I went through cartridge razors fairly quickly, and while I replace these razors with the same regularity, they're tons cheaper.

Unfortunately now I will have to check my luggage everywhere I go. Damned if I will switch back to those expensive cartridge razors for the convenience of being able to do carry-on.or itself does. column14: I have seen konjac sponges showing up in magazines and online, but I wasn’t really sure what they were so I did some research.  Turns out they are made from the root of the konjac plant so naturally I’m intrigued.  As fortune may have it I was given the opportunity to purchase the SpaWorks Konjac Exfoliating Facial Cleansing Sponge free of charge in exchange for my honest and unbiased review.  My order came with two individual packs each containing one sponge.  The sponges arrived rock hard, but holding one under warm water softened it right up.  Once wet it took on a rubbery texture and became very squishy and soft.  The sponge has a thin string running through it so that it can be hung which is nice for drying.  The sponge dries very fast which is great as I never feel like it gets that wet mildew scent that washcloths can get.  To use the sponge I added some facial cleaner and worked to a nice lather.  As a note you don’t need to use as much cleanser with the konjac sponge as you normally would.  Begin scrubbing your face in a circular motion, spending extra time in high problem areas.  After cleansing rinse your face and the sponge.  Hang the sponge to dry.  After using this sponge my face feels softer and I feel like I got a much better clean than I do just using my hands.  After using the konjac sponge I don’t think I will ever go back to washing my face with just my hands.

column13: “I still have my feet on the ground. I just wear better shoes.” Oprah Winfrey
column14:
I received this Rechargeable Callous Remover from FiveJoy for an honest review.

The very first thing I noticed for this item was its packaging. There is a place for everything and no wasted space. I like that!

The instruction booklet is user friendly and covers everything you need to know. It is written in readable English, (not like some manuals, I have received.) For an example of the wrong kind: Please donot disassembly it. You see what I mean?

The unit also comes with a handy fabric storage bag so you can dispose of the cardboard box. Each set has two heads so two people can use this remover in a household safely. It takes about 16 hours to charge it the first time and you should make sure you refresh the charge every 2-3 weeks to keep it ready to use.

It’s very simple to use, turn it on and away it goes. This is for your feet only and you should not use it too long because it can sand away too much skin if you aren’t careful. I found it quick and easy and it made the bottom of my feet smooth and soft. It worked wonderfully! I have not had this soft of feet for ages.

They do not recommend you use it if you have any open sores or scabs. I would suggest putting cream on your feet until that heals and then use this Electronic Callous Remover to do the rest of the job.

I love doing business with FiveJoy. The people I deal with are very caring and customer oriented. I have never had any problems with FiveJoy.

I recommend this Callous Remover for anyone with problem feet that have gotten hard on bottom or edges of your feet. It works and it is fast.

column6: Razorba Back Hair Shaver
column13: shaving the back suddenly becomes quite easy. I thought the product a bit expensive for ...
column14: The Razorba is an interesting product.  The product itself does little more than make it possible for one to reach areas of the back that are normally beyond our reach.  Of and by itself it does nothing at all.  The user is required to stick his razor (usually a disposable works just fine) in the opening provided on the Razorba.  Thus equipped, shaving the back suddenly becomes quite easy.  I thought the product a bit expensive for a hunk of plastic and bit more than half the price of a Mangroomer) but that said, the product does make back shaving simple.  Because one supplies his own razor, each shave can be as close as you wish.  As the disposable blade dulls (usually 6-8 shaves) simply replace it.  I had used a Mangroomer (much like an electric razor for the back) which required batteries and replacement once the blades wore out.  I am quite happy with the Razorba and recommend it.

column6: CoverGirl Face Products CoverGirl & Olay Simply Ageless Foundation, Natural Beige 240, 0.40-Ounce Package
column14: I've used this product for about 5 years now.  It covers better than any other foundation I've ever used.  I see that some of the reviews say it doesn't cover that well.  I have a lot of sun spots on my skin, and they really get darker in the summer.  I use a cover up before I apply the foundation so the spots don't show up at all for several hours.  (I only put it on once a day--I have a friend who dabs it on all day so her imperfections don't show all day).  I picked up one of my friends to go shopping the other day, and she looked at me and said, "Your skin looks like the skin of a young woman, it's so smooth and creamy looking."  I'm 69, and, though I do take care of my skin, I still feel that this product, (especially with a cover up on the sunspots), is what makes my skin look the way it does.  (Also I do circles w/ my fingers up and down from my jaw to my temples, and I find that the whole area has firmed up). column6: Energy Synergy Essential Oil Blend (Physical Energy). 100% Pure, Undiluted, Therapeutic Grade. (Blend of: Peppermint, Rosemary, Lemon and Eucalyptus)
column13: Helps me feel more awake when I'm tired
column14: I am not a morning person and lately I have really been not sleeping well and struggling with low energy and tiredness. I use peppermint oil in my room diffuser a lot as it both helps me feel more awake and alert, but also helps my sinuses open more so I can breathe better, especially during allergy season. I have lemon oil, but use it more for other things than in my diffuser, because lemon is very strong and citrus smells, even though I like them, tend to give me a headache very quickly. Thus it has never occurred to me to mix lemon with my peppermint. This is a blend of lemon, peppermint, eucalyptus, and rosemary, which is not a blend I likely would have thought to try on my own. I was struggling this morning so put several drops of this in my diffuser and let it fill the room while I was trying to work. I believe it did help me feel more awake and focused on my tasks. I did not find the lemon overpowering, but rather a nice citrus note mixed with the fresh coolness of the mint and eucalyptus. I was actually surprised to find that I liked this blend as much as I do given the lemon, but I think I will use it often on tired days. I received this oil at a promotional price for the purpose of product testing and feedback in the form of an honest and unbiased review. All opinions expressed are based on my personal experience with the product.

column6: Dove Men+Care Body Wash, Aqua Impact 18 oz
column13: Excellent Body Wash (But Dispenser Might Not Be For Everyone)
column14:
The first thing I noticed when I received this in the mail was that this is a big bottle of shower gel. If you're used to using Axe products like I am, you'll definitely notice the difference as Axe body gels come in 16 ounce bottles while this bottle is nearly 50% bigger. In terms of value, you're definitely getting more bang for your buck with this jumbo sized Dove body wash bottle.

The next thing I noticed was the top-sided gel dispenser which is also different from what I'm used to with my Axe body wash where I can simply squeeze the body of the bottle to get the gel out. If you don't have somewhere in your shower to place this on, needing to press down and dispense from the top can become a bit of a nuisance. Luckily for me I've got a ledge at a reasonable height level in my shower which makes this easy but other people might not be so lucky. With the bottle being so big, it is not easy to hold this bottle and dispense the gel at the same time.

That complaint aside, this gel has a great manly scent to it that is very fresh and not too harsh. It goes on easy and leaves me feeling fresh after using. If you can get past the wonky dispensing design, this is a great product to add to your shower gel mix.

I have had professional whitening done by my dentist, followed up by the "cheap" at home solutions used with my professional dentist tray to keep my teeth white as they do start to fade over time, regardless of whether you had it done at a dentist or not. Usually whitening toothpaste keeps the whiteness going for a good while longer than regular toothpaste, but I found this to be absolutely the best whitening product I've tried. After a brush in the morning, I feel there's definitely an improvement over my prior all-in-one (including whitening) toothpaste. The first step is a deep cleaning whitening toothpaste and there's a clear improvement after this step, but the real improvement comes with the finisher in step 2, which Crest calls a "whitening finisher." I noticed a very clear improvement immediately after brushing. I don't think this is intended to whiten teeth that haven't been treated before, but as a touch up for previously treated teeth and as a followup to the excellent Crest 3D Luxe whitening strips, this is a great product and one I'm definitely keeping in my cabinet.

column6: Olay Age Defying Classic Daily Renewal Cream Facial Moisturizer 2 Oz
column13: Good for my sensitive, hashimoto's thyroid skin!
column14:
It's highly unusual (read: I never have) that I buy a beauty cream more than once. I just finished my second bottle, and I'm back for a third.

My stats: sensitive, combination skin, hypothyroid, 45 years, female, active, outdoorsy, swimmer, hiker, equestrian, sun worshipper, water drinker

This product does not irritate my skin, or cause breakouts. I've been using it for 1.5 years, but don't use it during very cold winter weather. It isn't enough moisturizer to handle my outdoor lifestyle in the freezing cold. I don't hold that against it because not much does. I consider it a three season daily use item, with it being insufficient to combat the northeast winters of NY.

I have seen a definite reduction in wrinkles (crows feet, marionette lines). I don't have any deep lines, but the more shallow lines are much better after about 2 weeks daily use. My skin feels softer, more elastic, and has has a smoother texture. I get complimented frequently on how nice it looks. I notice if I don't use it after almost a week.

The texture is slightly viscous, and moves easily on the skin. The consistency is like that of hyaluronic acid, but with a touch of cream. It isn't watery, and is not nearly as heavy as something like cold cream. The color is off white with warm overtones (I don't know why I thought I should write that, but there you have it).

I use two presses of the tube for my entire face.

Lightly fragranced, but not enough to offend my slightly sensitive nose. It's not a natural smelling fragrance, though..not chemical, just lightly scented. I'm not the fragrance police type...just fussy about smelling too perfume-like.

Overall this has performed as advertised for me, and I will continue to use it as long as it does. I have no expectations that it will stop doing so.

column6: Pure Body Naturals Cold Pressed Castor Oil for Hair Growth & Skin Care, Hexane-Free, 16 Fl. Oz
column13: Great oil, works well for what I use it for.
column14:
Castor oil is something that I use quite frequently around my home, We use it for so many things. We naturally use it for the most popular reason people get castor oil, our hair. We use it for dry scalp which four out of the five us in my home suffer from. I used it for my children when that had cradle cap as babies and it works great for that. I also use it for dry itchy skin in the winter time. It has anti-fungal and antibacterial benefits which is something that first attracted me to castor oil. I have used it as a lubricant for scissors, to help repair split ends on my hair, in place of chapstick, as a massage oil, I have used it on my nails and my daughter even uses it to help with her acne. There is just so much we use it for on a daily basis.

This particular brand is a great one. It absorbs well. It comes in a bottle that is going to last for a long time since with castor oil I have never had to use much, it spreads very easily. I love the flip top lid that comes with it. It makes it very easy to get the oil directly where your aiming for without making a mess with it. The oil is cold pressed and is the same consistency of other castor oils I have used. I am happy with this brand and will use it in the future.

column6: Aria Starr Beauty ORGANIC Argan Oil (4 OZ) For Hair, Skin, Face, Nails, Beard & Cuticles - Best 100% Pure Moroccan Anti Aging, Anti Wrinkle Beauty Secret, EcoCert Certified Cold Pressed Moisturizer
column14:
This is an awesome oil! It's a bright, clear, pale straw-colored clean oil with a very mild, almost-not-there fresh scent. The dropper bottle is easy to use and the oil seems like it's high quality.

The first time I tried argan oil, I put a number of drops on one arm, and initially was not too happy because it left my arm feeling slightly oily for a long time. I wiped the excess off and it was fine. Later that night, I noticed the skin of that arm was deliciously soft. Smooth, pettable soft. *Perfect* soft.

I've since decided that the oiliness was my fault; I simply used too much. That's great, because this is an expensive luxury oil and if a few drops will cover a large area, that's perfect. My next discovery: after getting out of the shower, while your skin is still slightly damp, apply some argan oil. It will help retain some of that moisture, and the damp will help you spread a small amount of oil more easily. It made my skin feel amazing. Dare I suggest this treatment if you have a romantic evening planned?

column6: Make Up For Ever AQUA CREAM 53 Pearly Light Lagoon Green Full size 0.21 oz
column13: Rich shimmer, but kind of creasy
column14:
This eyeshadow is a pleasant color, and is SUPER shimery. At first glance, it seemed to be kinda dried out, but once I started to use it, it was creamy as expected. You get a pretty good amount in the tub, but it creases easily so a primer is recommended. Without a primer, a little will stay put and provide a pale shimmer but you won't get the color (see the picture, the middle is with multiple layers to get the minty green color, the outsides are with one swipe). This effect could be good with other colors (use one layer as a highlight color, and some deeper colors for the lid/corners). column13: Best shave gel I've ever used.
column14:
I can't say enough good things about this product. Ever since I started using it, I have only had one instance of razor burn (because I didn't apply enough of the gel). I used to get razor burn at least 3 or 4 times a month, but now I can go many months without ever having a single instance. I have used the King of Shaves product for over 2 years (although this particular scent I've used for a little more than 4 months).

I have a very precisely trimmed beard that requires some rough re-shaping every so often, but this gel has done wonders with protecting my skin. Plus, it goes on clear, so you can shave as precisely as needed without having to worry about foam or suds being in your line of sight while shaving.

The scent of it is very citrus-like, and it's really pleasant. I'm a big fan of citrus scented items, and this definitely delivers with its clean and fresh scent.

If you have any issues with razor burn, or just want a good clear shave gel, I highly suggest this product.

Note - you need to give the shave gel a couple of shaves to work. This is because the aloe penetrates the skin's layers, and as you shed those outer layer cells, newer and better protected/hydrated cells will take their place. After the 3rd or 4th shave you will really notice the difference.

column6: RainbowWigs Western Women Short Lady's Full Hair Wigs
column13: I have been shorn like a sheep.
column14:
I went to a new stylist who evidently took an instant dislike to me. Maybe I reminded her of her daughter-in-law, the beer guzzling tramp. Maybe I looked like the IRS agent who informed her that she owed a fortune in penalties and interest.

For thirty minutes, she pressed her chest in my face or lifted her arm so that my nose and her armpit became old and dear friends. (I never again want to be that close to a strange woman). She distinguished herself by cutting my lovely locks to about 3/4" all over my head. Then she proceeded to tell me how cute I looked. Yeah, for a guy! Or a Marine recruit!

I look like I've recently recovered from chemotherapy and my hair's just started to grow out. Or like I've been a prisoner of war.

Thank heavens for this wig. I've worn it now for a month. Can you believe it? My hair is still shorter than this wig. In fact, this wig is long compared to my hair. I've gotten compliments on my new hairstyle.

I've never worn a wig, but then I've never been reduced to looking like this, either. It looks pretty good, but then anything looks better than I do at the moment.

I used it in all areas at full strength (legs, underarms, nether regions) and found that while I did notice delayed growth in terms of the hair growing back after shaving as well as thinned hair on my legs, I didn't experience Hair "Removal" which is how this is marketed. column6: Conair Infiniti Pro Translucent Styler
column13: Dries super fast, and leaves hair shiny and static-free
column14:
Over the years I've owned over a dozen Conair dryers - starting back in the big-hair '80s. They're usually long lasting, inexpensive and get the job done. None of my older models had anything fancy about them, so I was interested in trying this Infiniti Pro with ceramic and ionic technology. I've heard that these make hair shiny and smooth and reduce the damage from blow-drying.

I used it today and I really liked it. It's lightweight so my arm didn't get tired of holding it, and my hair dried in half the time it usually takes. My hair looked shiny and it behaved after styling so the ceramic/ionic technology actually does improve the appearance of hair. I used the diffuser to lift at the roots and my hair had lots of volume. I tried the concentrator when I curled my bangs, and that also worked well. I'm not a big fan of the bright pink color, but my college-age daughters both loved it. The only thing that could make this dryer better is if the handle folded for traveling. It's not a huge dryer, but when packing a suitcase I'll still take my little travel sized Conair dryer.

Features:
- Pretty pink and metallic design (also available in blue)
- Comes with a diffuser and a concentrator attachment to make styling easy
- Dries hair faster than my current Conair dryer
- Loop for hanging on a hook
- Ceramic/ionic technology makes hair more shiny, smooth and static-free
- Cold shot button for setting curls
- Buttons for Low/High options for Hot/Warm/Cool drying
- lightweight for its size

Overall I really like this hair dryer. It dried my hair much faster than my old dryer, and left my hair looking great. At nearly $40 I think it's a little overpriced, but if it does a fast job and makes my hair look nice, maybe it's worth it.

column6: Sedu Icon Styling Iron
column13: Comparing the Icon and the Diamond
column14:
So let me start off by saying that I normally do not review products. However, I thought it was needed for this particular item as there isn't much out there in the way of reviews comparing the Sedu Revolution Diamond Styling Iron and the Sedu Icon Styling Iron. I would have benefited greatly from a review similar to the one I am about to post.
I had the original Sedu Revolution for almost 3 years and loved it, but eventually it stopped working and it was time for a new one. I was torn between these two later models as I was able to get them both around the same price due to a special deal online. I first ordered the Icon and was disappointed immediately with the quality. It was an orange plastic material that did not feel sturdy and "creaked" when I would use it. I ordered the Diamond edition about ten minutes after opening the box of the Icon, prepared to return the Icon when the diamond arrived. I used the Icon for a few days while waiting for the diamond, and I was actually pretty pleased with the results when straightening my hair. It is a good iron, but not worth over $100 in my opinion. The Diamond arrived and I could already tell it was made with a better material that was sturdier, and looks much nicer. Also, when comparing how they glide through hair (after using It's A 10 spray product), the Diamond is much, much smoother. This will be essential when using the styling iron to curl hair.
The irons are almost exactly, physically the same other than color and the name printed on the iron. I liked the auto-shut off on both and the temperature at 340 is perfect for my long, naturally wavy hair. I ended up deciding to go with the Diamond from how smoothly it ran through my hair compared to the Icon, and how much stronger and well-made it felt. I will be returning the Icon.

Bottom line: Both the Diamond and the Icon are wonderful and very similar irons, but the Diamond seems to be better made and runs through the hair more smoothly than the Icon.

column6: Manic Panic Amplified Flash Lightning 40 Hair Bleach
column13: Excellent home lightener, especially for platinum blonde
column14:
Back in the 90s, I bleached my hair all the time. I was used to a 30 volume home kit that took forever to work on my dark brown hair, even with root coverage. (90 minutes plus, covered.)

I went with Manic Panic now because it's a brand I trust. The kit has everything you need to bleach: powder, developer creme, gloves, brush, and mixing bowl.

Now that I have the Internet to help, I learned a few things:
1. Slather on coconut oil for a few hours before bleaching. This helped prevent fried ends. My hair is so soft after treating, and looks much more natural.
2. Wrapping is important. Heat helps accelerate the bleaching. After wrapping my hair in plastic cling wrap, it took half an hour to get the results I wanted. I was truly shocked at how fast this 40 volume worked on my dark brown roots.
3. Toning - if you want that bleached look, stop here. But if you want platinum, get some toner! I bought Wella Color Charm T18 (White Ash Blonde) and their 20 volume developer creme, and applied it to mostly dried bleached hair. 10 minutes later, and I had awesome gray/platinum (which could easily be waaaay purple if left on too long). The purple balances out the Orange/brassy tones left from bleaching. I get tons of compliments on my hair, even questions if it's natural.

I could see how this could easily fry your hair if you're used to a weaker bleaching solution, so beware. Check your roots frequently for color to avoid crispy ends. But especially if you have dark hair, this works really well.

column6: Crest 3D White Brilliance Toothpaste, Teeth Whitening and Deep Cleansing via Daily Two-Step System, 4.0 Oz and 2.3 Oz Tubes
column14:
I was super excited to try this new two step system. I received it from BzzAgent and Crest to try for free #GotItFree. I have sensitive teeth and gums so using the strips is actually painful. This seemed like it was right up my alley. It's a pretty simple procedure.

Step 1 - brush with the deep cleanse toothpaste for one minute. Don't rinse.
Step 2 - brush with the whitening gel for one minute. Rinse.

Step one was interesting. I felt like it did a really good job of cleaning and it left my breath pretty minty. It had a gritty texture to it and after a minute I started getting a squeaky clean feel. It was interesting to say the least, but it was a mental indicator that maybe it was working really well.
Step two was nice because it cleaned off all of that gritty toothpaste from step one. It left my teeth smooth and they felt really clean.

As for the whitening, meh. I wasn't all that impressed. I felt that there were some days that my teeth looked whiter, but at the end of two weeks, I didn't see that much of a difference. Maybe a shade or two lighter but it wasn't really enough for me to be like, "Oh! I see the white!" I will keep using it to see where it takes me, but after two weeks I'm not all that optimistic. I think it did a great job cleaning but that was about it. I DO drink a lot of tea and periodically have a diet soda so maybe there is just too much staining on my teeth already for the product to do a good enough job.It was also nice that it didn't hurt my teeth or gums like the strips do.
