I've been purchasing random concealers recommended in different youtube beauty reviews. I've tried this, the Makeup Forever HD waterproof concealer, and Nars radiant concealer. This is #2 for me (Nars is #1) but does have its own good things.

Pros:
Love the pump instead of a stick or tube. Stick is ok. Tube (MUFE) is bad.
This is thick - so for the darkest circles it really covers (MUFE isn't bad).

Cons
Somehow slightly harder to blend than the Nars. Either I don't blend enough and its a thick layer - or it blends completely off and I need to re-apply.
Also, its not as luminizing as the nars and I have to use a separate luminizer.

For me Nars stick makes it awkward - but its the easiest to blend, doesn't settle into my lines, "bakes" well under powder to set it - and I dont' need a separate luminizer.

column14: These were a major disappointment. First of all, they barely heated after 15 minutes. Secondly, five rollers is not going to roll your whole head of hair unless you have extremely thin hair. So, for me, I had to roll 1/3 of my head (yes, I have lots of thick shoulder-length hair), wait to roll the next third, and wait again to roll the final third. On the plus side, I will say that even though it didn't curl my thick frizzy hair, it did straighten it nicely and get rid of the frizz which is great if  you wanted straightened hair. I did not.

column6: Sunny Isle Extra Dark Jamaican Black Castor Oil, 8 oz
column14:
I have been coloring my (originally blonde) hair since I was 12 years old, and for the last 7 years have been attempting to grow my hair out. (I had had it very short for a while.) But with all the coloring, I would end up needing to cut if off again.

This time around, I have been growing it for a year and a half. I'd had it in a pixie cut, and it's finally made it to my shoulders. Unfortunately, I'd also been coloring my hair every two weeks for a while now, but in the last month alone, I'd colored it THREE times. I also made the mistake of using a supposedly natural shampoo on my hair instead of a salon shampoo. Long story short, my hair was a brittle MESS. I didn't know what to do besides cut it all off again. I really wanted long hair, but, I said, it's clear my hair doesn't look good long.

Then I read an article about essential oils for your beauty cabinet, and this was in it. I thought, why not. The instructions assume you will be treating your hair once per week, but because a)I have the free time necessary to really treat my hair, and b)I had a hair appointment not far off and wanted to try to save my hair before going so that the stylist order me to have it cut (which I really didn't want to do).

So over the last week, I have treated my hair with this stuff three times. I mix it with Sweet Almond oil, which makes it easier to apply, and I work it through my hair, especially the ends, and rub my scalp with it. I spend about 10 minutes doing this. Then I put a plastic shower cap on it and just leave it for as long as I can stand the shower cap (about two to three hours). Then I run my blow dryer over the the cap for 15 minutes (I don't have a hood dryer). Then I rinse it out and shampoo and style as usual.

The upshot: It works miracles. I have NEVER in my life known what it's like to have soft, shiny, healthy hair that moves. But now it does! Almost all of the damage that can be reversed has been. I can't believe I've been fooling around with expensive deep conditioners all this time and getting almost nothing for it--this is really all I ever needed.

About my hair: my hair is naturally wavy, baby-fine, but I do have a lot of it (it is not thinning in any way). I am also white. I do hope that my hair will grow faster and thicker with this, but won't know for a while if it does do that. I plan to use this on my eyebrows as well, since overplucking my once glorious eyebrows has left them anemic.

column6: Remington D8700 T|Studio PROtect Dryer, Aquatic Green
column14:
This dryer has a 3-heat setting (high, medium, and cool) and 2 speed setting (high and low). It works great with the medium and high heat. The "cool" shot (and cool setting) is not quite as cool as some of my prior hair dryers and it also takes a few seconds longer to actually produce the cooler temperature. Having said that, it does still lock in my style with use of a round brush. This 1875 Watt hair dryer dries my medium length (and medium texture) hair very quickly. I should also note that the High heat setting doesn't feel like it is scorching your scalp.

I really didn't notice any difference with the "Conditioning Technology." This is a ring attachment that is the circumference of the nozzle. You simply twist this ring onto the nozzle where the hot air blows out (you could easily take this on and off – I choose to simply leave mine on all the time so I don’t lose it) and use your dryer like normal. It is supposed to release "micro-conditioners" as you blow dry your hair. Ingredients for the condition ring includes Macadamina Nut Oil and Argan Oil (Argan Oil is expressed from the seeds of the Argan tree what is native to Southwestern Morocco). Although I’m not noticing a huge positive with this technology – of equal importance, I’m also not achieving a hair style that is too soft (due to OVER conditioning). So overall, I’m neutral with the conditioning technology that is incorporated into this dryer. If you have dry brittle hair – maybe your results will be more noticeable.

You'll receive a complementary hair brush with this dryer. It has plastic bristles with plastic tips - nothing fancy but I like the brush.

I included a picture of what you receive with your dryer. The color of the dryer is silver and metallic green - it's sleek looking and light weight (only weighs in around 20-21 ounces). This dryer feels of lighter weight than my last one which is a bonus. I use the bulky 3M removable clips on my wall and the hanging loop is wide enough to accommodate this hook.

The diffuser and concentrator are made of a light green plastic - this color isn't very attractive. The diffuser and concentrator have to be twisted onto the nozzle and neither stays on very tightly (my prior hair brushes merely snapped into place - this option seemed a lot more secure). If I accidentally bump the nozzle when the diffuser or concentrator is in use, it's not uncommon that the attachments disengage from the nozzle - This is rather inconvenient and is the major drawback with this product. Fortunately, I don't use these attachments often so the fact that they fall off rather easily doesn't really impact my daily use.

This is a better than average hair dryer despite the issues with the attachments. I've owned other Remington hair dryers and I consider them to be reliable. My prior Remingtons have lasted at least 4-years (with daily use) before I selected a new one. Often my reason for upgrading to a new one is mainly due to the cruddy appearance the hair dryer begins to take on through the years due to dust build up in vents and hair spray residue that I can no longer wipe off rather than a decrease in performance.

column6: THE FACE SHOP Spin 4D Vibration Pore Brush/Auto Make-up Foundation[Stylebang]
column13: This brush's construction and durability is not the best at all
column14: Alright, so I bought this vibration pore brush in order to help make sure my cleanser really gets into my skin, and this product claims to do this. It is true that when I first tested it out, the product did seem to give off that effect. I was quite happy with it because the brushes were what seemed extremely high quality and not irritating to the skin at all. A lot of the reviews claimed how it didn't really make people break out like what other vibration spinning brushes do and I experienced the same thing. The whole reason I bought this product was that it wasn't incredibly expensive like the clairsonic, and the reviews even compared its quality to the clairsonic.  After using it for awhile, I would say that people who compare it to the clairsonic are making quite a huge mistake.  The big difference between this face shop brush and the clairsonic would lie in the durability and the construction of this product. After using it for a week, the results was as the product describes, however I am not sure if the product I received was defective (pretty sure it wasn't because it worked for the first week), but after awhile of continuous use the brush pieces would not connect to the main body of the brush. The brush and body of the brush are connected by quite a flexible, black thin rubber material (or at least mine was quite flimsy). This rubber material is what causes the brush to spin, and when I noticed that it had broken I questioned why such a thin mechanic was used and expected to last for long. If you look at the image, you will see what I am talking about when I say the middle section broke off. I was appalled because I had not remove the brush incorrectly, yet it literally turned brittle and was stuck in the brush head when I gently removed it.  My hopes is that if you plan on buying this product you be VERY careful with attaching the brush head, and VERY careful when taking it off, because this product might not be worth its money in that it doesn't seem likea very long term product. The material is quite fragile, and I am now pretty much left with a useless brush and brush pieces that will not attach to the main body because of either the specific product I received, or even the product itself (each of them). I found it sort of questionable why they don't even sell replacement brushes, but I figured you're probably meant to keep buying the brush. I was quite unsatisfied with this buying experience and I'm very disappointed because I had really high expectations for this product. This would actually be my first time experiencing this in all my Amazon purchases, and I'm quite sad to say it was from one my favorite brands "The Face Shop".

column6: Sedu Revolution Diamond Styling Iron
column14:
So let me start off by saying that I normally do not review products. However, I thought it was needed for this particular item as there isn't much out there in the way of reviews comparing the Sedu Revolution Diamond Styling Iron and the Sedu Icon Styling Iron. I would have benefited greatly from a review similar to the one I am about to post.
I had the original Sedu Revolution for almost 3 years and loved it, but eventually it stopped working and it was time for a new one. I was torn between these two later models as I was able to get them both around the same price due to a special deal online. I first ordered the Icon and was disappointed immediately with the quality. It was an orange plastic material that did not feel sturdy and "creaked" when I would use it. I ordered the Diamond edition about ten minutes after opening the box of the Icon, prepared to return the Icon when the diamond arrived. I used the Icon for a few days while waiting for the diamond, and I was actually pretty pleased with the results when straightening my hair. It is a good iron, but not worth over $100 in my opinion. The Diamond arrived and I could already tell it was made with a better material that was sturdier, and looks much nicer. Also, when comparing how they glide through hair (after using It's A 10 spray product), the Diamond is much, much smoother. This will be essential when using the styling iron to curl hair.
The irons are almost exactly, physically the same other than color and the name printed on the iron. I liked the auto-shut off on both and the temperature at 340 is perfect for my long, naturally wavy hair. I ended up deciding to go with the Diamond from how smoothly it ran through my hair compared to the Icon, and how much stronger and well-made it felt. I will be returning the Icon.

Bottom line: Both the Diamond and the Icon are wonderful and very similar irons, but the Diamond seems to be better made and runs through the hair more smoothly than the Icon.
Attached is a photo comparison of the irons. I used the diamond on one side of my head, and the icon on the other, as labeled. I saw almost no difference between the two after using them on my hair.

column6: Secure Sensitive Denture Adhesive, 1.4 oz
column13: Secure is by far the best dental adhesive that I have found
column14: Secure is by far the best dental adhesive that I have found. I use either Prosoft or DIY (which doesn't leave the nasty taste in your mouth that Prosoft does) professional soft reline kit to reline both my top and bottom plates.  Because my gums are sensitive I need the soft liner to add a cushion between the dentures and my gums.  Without the soft liner I can not wear them.  The dentures hurt!  I use Secure to hold my dentures in place while eating. For the first time since I have had my dentures (7 years) I can finally eat without food particles getting underneath my plates causing pain and irritation or my lower plate lifting and moving all around. I got the Secure for sensitive gums and I am completely happy with this product and it's effectiveness. I've had no problems with burning or irritated gums as others have stated they have and I have very sensitive gums.  I also had no problem removing my dentures after I swished warm water around in my mouth (several times.)  I removed Secure from my dentures with warm water and a toothbrush and then soaked them in my usual denture cleaner (Fixodent antibacterial denture cleaner plus scope tablets.)  I will no longer use anything else and trust me I've tried everything.  This stuff is awesome!

column13: I am normally a bleach blonde with super thin hair
column14:
I am normally a bleach blonde with super thin hair. I personally hate how bleached out my hair looks during the summer. My hair stylist usually puts low lights in my hair to break it up. I personally wanted something a little different and died my hair dark brown at the beginning of the summer. My hair didn't take well with the box dye and has been a little dry since. I decided to give this a try since its oil based. My hair definitely doesn't feel as dry as it did before and got rid of my way to white for a 22 year old roots. I ended up using my personal gloves for the process because I ripped the ones they gave me on accident. The bottle looks really cool but was really hard to hold onto as everyone has already mentioned. I feel like I was using higher end products based on the bottles but it seemed wasteful at the same time.

Overall I am really happy so far with the product. I LOVE that there is no ammonia and is oil based. This is waaay safer to use and put on your body. I will certainly keep using the product vs $150 salons.

column6: Retseliney Acne-Treatment Oil-Control Moisturizer Cream with 2% Salicylic Acid and Vitamin C
column13: Oil Control and Hydration In One!
column14:
I'm not a fan of the fact that I still get acne in my mid-20s, and try to do whatever I can to prevent it. This blemish-control moisturizer from Retseliney has been a great way to control my breakouts and keep my face hydrated!

I love using natural ingredients on my skin, and the benefits this moisturizer provides are all naturally derived! This moisturizer contains witch hazel which is an excellent natural source of salicylic acid. The juniper cleanses and tones while I hydrate my skin, and the included vitamin C repairs sun damage beautifully!

My skin can be very dry, especially after cleansing. I was very pleased to find that this moisturizer hydrated my skin perfectly without leaving me feeling greasy at all! A small amount of this moisturizer goes a long way and I found that I only need about three pumps on even my driest days. Since there's cayenne in this lotion I get the moisture I need while still getting natural oil control!

This moisturizer became part of my daily routine as soon as I tried it, and it (along with its mask and cleanser counterparts, also available) has been a wonderful way to keep my face under control! I was provided with a sample of this moisturizer but price doesn't change how great my skin feels, nor does it effect my review.

column14: I'm always in search of a good powder foundation and I like this brand so I was pleased to find this in a sample size. I'm hesitant to purchase a full size when I'm testing out makeup but even more so when it's not a drug store brand. Read through the directions first as they specify how to apply this to get the best results. This powder was easy to use. The mini brush that came with it was functional but too stiff for my preference and too small for every day use. I applied the powder to the brush, taping off any excess and used a circular buffing motion to apply. I normally use a BB cream with the lightest touch so it took a few tries to get the right amount of light coverage. The makeup lasted all day and didn't feel caked on or heavy. The color was not a good choice for my skin tone though. I am fair but this shade left a yellow look to my skin. I would consider trying a different shade to see if I get better results. I received a discounted price to purchase this product in exchange for leaving a ewview.

column6: The Honest Company Honest Sunscreen Lotion SPF 30 2-pack 3.0oz
column14: I'm giving this product a 1 star  because I can't think of any positives related to it.  I purchased this two pack of sunscreen from a local warehouse because I thought it was a good deal and because I thought it was a healthier alternative to traditional chemical laden sunscreens. I'm not sure if the latter is true, but the former is not, since it was absolutely not effective in any way and was just a waste of money.  First, this product goes on very heavy--consistency and smell is similar to melted wax.  It does not rub into the skin very well and is not at all moisturizing.  In fact, I would say that it actually dries your skin out.  As far as wear throughout the day, this product seemed to cause me to sweat a lot more than usual.  I am generally not a noticeable sweater, but this product brought forth the sweat beads like no other. Not only that, it was was hard to miss the fact that I was sweating because the sweat condensed on the skin in the form of white ooze, so i looked like a melting wax sculpture.  As for sun protection, that is non-existent.  I had a noticeable color line from my where my clothing ended and where my skin began even though I applied a heavy coating of this sunscreen (since it's really the only option you have since it doesn't apply well).  I'm putting this out on the curb for some other sucker to have.

column13: Nice for massage or just as a candle
column14:
The Fantasy Massage Oil Candle has a delicate floral scent that I can't actually pin down, but I found it to be pleasant, soothing, and not overpowering. This is a generously sized 10 oz candle made from sustainably grown, environmentally friendly, clean burning and long lasting USA grown soybeans and pure essential oils.

This hand poured soy candle burns slower and cooler than paraffin wax, has a pure cotton wick for clean, soot free burning, burns cleaner than paraffin candles, contains no toxins, carcinogens or pollutants, which means it's less likely to trigger allergies, and it doesn't give off any petrol-carbon soot like you get from paraffin candles. It's 100% natural as well, and the scent comes entirely from pure essential oils. So, in addition to smelling heavenly, this candle is a healthy addition to your home candle supply as well.

I found candle's floral scent soothing and relaxing, and could easily imagine burning it while I soaked in the garden tub, then massaging the melted wax onto my arms and legs to moisturize my skin. Under the right circumstances I wouldn't turn down a bit of warm wax massage action using this candle either! I did rub some warm wax from the candle on my arm just to see what it was like and it glided on like a warm rich lotion and left me scented like the candle. I do wish the candle came with a pour spout to make it a little easier to get the warm wax. This is definitely a high quality all natural, hand poured soy candle that's suitable for personal enjoyment or as a gift.

column6: Majestic Pure Carrier Oil, 4 oz
column13: good - reduced redness - didn't diminish acne marks - OXIDIZED QUICKLY - MUST TRANSFER TO A BOTTLE WITH A PUMP!
column14:
Ok, you guys. I used this for oil cleansing (and I use a microfiber towel damped in warm water to rinse it off). Then I would cleanse my face with raw honey right after. And then I would use two drops of this as my moisturizer, wait for my face to dry, then apply Vitamin C serum. I stopped breaking out with cystic acne HOWEVER this may be because I no longer use detergent to wash my face, and I'm letting my natural oil layer come back to life to protect my skin. I used it over the course of two weeks. I saw improvement on decreasing redness of my face. But it didn't clear out my acne marks -- which what I was aiming for. But this may be because I only used it through the course of two weeks.

column6: Anti Cellulite Coffee Kona Scrub with Dead Sea Salts - 24oz - All Natural - Coffee Scrubs Are Great Body Scrubs for Reducing Cellulite and Stretch Marks
column14:
I received this product yesterday just in time for my morning shower. Thanks mail lady! The product in the picture looks a little different than what I received. In the picture the package looks very full. I am aware that it is 8 ounces of product but the package that I have is very flat and less than half full. I purchased the grapefruit and lemongrass variety because it is supposed to help with acne, age spots, skin discoloration, dull complexion and cellulite. I thought it would help with some skin discoloration and body acne that I have.

I really love that this scrub has all natural ingredients that I can pronounce and I actually know what they are. Dead Sea Salt, Organic Kona Coffee, Organic Olive Oil, Organic Sweet Almond Oil, Organic Grapeseed Oil, Coffee Arabica See Oil, Organic Shea Butter, Natural Fragrance Extracts.

I must admit that this scrub is very fragrant. The scrub is not as abrasive as other scrubs that I have used. The scrub was very easy to rinse of and left no traces of greasy residue. After my shower I noticed my skin was very softer and a little smoother. I can not say if this scrub eliminates cellulite, I have quite a bit of it and I believe one use of this scrub will not make it go away but my skin was noticeably smoother.

It's kind of hard to scoop the product out of the bag and use it without being wasteful. It's also hard to seal the bag and make sure it stays shut. I plan to find a glass jar to transfer the product in so that it can last longer. The packaging can definitely be improved. I plan on using this scrub like twice a week. Besides the packaging issues I think this is a really good scrub.

I have received a discount on this product in exchange for my honest and unbiased review. I enjoy writing reviews and put a lot of effort into how I feel about the products. I think it is important as consumers to make a well informed decision before purchasing a product.in exchange for my honest review but opinions are all my own.

column6: Majestic Pure Essential Oil, 100% Pure and Natural with Therapeutic Grade, Premium Quality Oil 4fl
column13: Great Deal for a Convenient Dropper and Size, Scent is Great in Air, But Up Close?
column14:
While I've used a lot of essential oils in the past, and a lot of lavender oils, I was enticed by the size of this oil as well as the included dropper than screws into the top of the bottle. These make it very easy to distribute the oil into a filter for air conditioning or a sachet, as well as a diffuser. I tried it in a carrier oil as well and my sensitive skin suffered no ill effects.

...I just feel like this oil is.... cut with something like an alcohol, strangely enough. The smell is a liiiittle bit "off", while retaining that familiar lavender scent, I get a mix of something else a bit stringent. It could be the variety of lavender plant used as the bottle states it comes from Bulgaria, so you could chalk this up to general ignorance about plant extracts, which is entirely possible.

So I tried a silly test. I dropped this brand of oil on a cheesecloth next to a brand of lavender essential oil I got from Whole Foods. You know that oily greasy stain? It speads out like a little bit and sets in. While my other brand spead out about an inch and stayed like this after four hours, the Majestic Pure spread out two inches in diameter. Again, could be a carrier or it's cut with something, or the pressing process allowing for a lighter weight oil.

I actually struggled with this review because the price is great for a 4 ounce container, as well as including the dropper with a separate cap as well makes for a great buy. But I get the feeling something is a little off.

I say if you are using this for scent distribution or in a diffuser, you won't have a problem. If you are cutting with a carrier or lotion, you may pick up on the scent, especially if you are accustomed to other brands of essential lavender oil. If that makes sense.

I could just be "picky", and if anyone wants to clarify on the processes that may affect the viscosity or manufacturing process that affects scents between batches, feel free and I will update the review and bump it up to five stars.

I say go for it! It's going to last you forever in a diffuser or satchet and when carried through the air you won't notice the alcoholic scent, just the sweet and relaxing notes of classic lavender!and I will update the review and bump it up to five stars.

column6: Double Edge Safety Razor
column13: You deserve a shave this good!
column14:
This razor arrived on a day when I was wearing three days of stubble, so I broke it out, took a deep breath, and started shaving. In a word, AMAZING.

I've had a straight razor shave from a third-generation barber in Little Italy in New York, and this was the closest thing to that I've ever had. The next morning it seemed redundant to shave again, but I did just for the experience. Yes, I was a bit slower due to overabundant caution, but a couple weeks later I'm breezing through confidently. I also shave my head and was concerned about doing it with a double-edge razor, since I have a large scar on my head where I can't see it to be careful. No problem! The short handle means you don't need that silly flex head because the handle isn't hitting your collar bone or the heel of your hand.

Everyone says use a light hand and no pressure... totally true! Imagine you're shaving a balloon, and it's easy. Vincenzo, the barber in New York used remarkably short strokes, so I emulate that, and get what other people can clearly see is a closer shave without irritation. Jump in! I'm going to save $200 every year or more on not buying the plastic throw-away (already garbage the day they're made) cartridges. Save the planet and your wallet, and shave like a man. Go ahead. You deserve this razor!

column6: Majestic Pure Essential Oil, 100% Pure and Natural with Therapeutic Grade, Premium Quality Oil 4fl
column14:
Tea tree oil has only recently started to get any kind of a reputation. I have known for years that there were about an encyclopedia's worth of uses and applications for the body and around the house. It really is a handy helper.

It's great for cleaning both the skin (a wound) and as a component to a homemade cleaner for the house. One of the most important things to me at this time of year, it that it is a natural repellant against lice. My daughter goes into 4th grade tomorrow and there have been issues at her school with head lice. Diluting 10 drops of the oil into a small spray bottle (about 16oz or so) and using it to style her hair before school every day ensures that she will not fall victim to the horror that is a lice infestation. She has hair all the way down to her waist and I don't desire to pull nits out of that nor have to cut it. It's a real lifesaver if your child is school age and tends to be in an at-risk environment.

That same spray dilution is also great to help disinfect knee scrapes, scratches and minor cuts. It also helps to get stains (like grass) out of the kids' laundry. Aside from what I have mentioned, a quick search on the internet will show a ton of ways you can use tea tree oil to make natural, and EFFECTIVE, products and remedies at home. My fingers would cramp before I could explain how many different uses this 4oz bottle can be put to!

column6: As Seen On TV Shimmer Metallic Jewelry Tattoos
column14:
These Shimmer Metallic Jewelry Tattoos are easy to apply. Simply pick the design you want, peel off the covering of the tattoo, place the tattoo on the spot you want to wear it, wet a sponge or paper towel and hold it on the tattoo for thirty seconds, remove the sponge or paper towel, peel off the paper from the tattoo and you have a tattoo!

I love these tattoos! Somebody gave them to me as a bit of a joke but I (and everyone in my office) fell in love with them. There were two sheets of silver tattoos and two sheets of gold tattoos so you have plenty to pick from. My favorites are the ones that I can wear like bracelets. The tattoos are very easy to apply and, while they won't look like real tattoos under close scrutiny, I did fool a few people who thought they were real. How long they last depends on where you wear them - I find they last at least a week before starting to fade away. With seventy tattoos there are more than enough to pick from and you'll surely find something you like.

I love these Shimmer Metallic Jewelry Tattoos!

column6: Tan Towel Half Body Plus Self-Tan Towelettes 10 Pack
column13: Ok For A Quick Weekend Tan.
column14:
Ok for a quick tan if you are only needing it to last for the weekend. I was expecting better results though after reading other reviews. Here is my low down on this product.

Pros:
Goes on easily, without the mess of a lotion.

Not too orange.

Fades like a normal tan.

Does not smell bad.

Cons:
Does not last. On average the tan only lasts about two days.

One towel does not cover half the body. ( I am normal sized and I found that it takes at least 3 towels to do my legs, arms, back, and chest.)

Expensive. If you only had to use one towel each time, the price might be affordable, but since you must use several towels each time and the tan only lasts about 2 days, it can be quite expensive.

Very light. The tan you get from one use is a very light tan. So if you have any sort of color already or if you are looking for a darker golden color, you will surely need to do two applications.

The towels dry too quickly. Once you open the pack you have about 2 minutes to use the towel before it completely dries.

Final Thoughts:
This product is easy to apply and the tan appears rather quickly. The tan however, does not last long and you will most likely need to use 3-4 towels to do your whole body and achieve the desired color. I think this product would be good to use for a wedding, special event, or a weekend vacation where you simply want to look tan for a couple days. However, with the price what it is, I can not see using this product several times a week year round, as it would be way too expensive.

column6: Dove Men+Care Spray Gel, Control & Medium Hold Thickening 6.7 oz
column13: Best Applied With Hands Not Sprayed, Great Hold
column14:
The Dove Men+Care Thickening Spray Gel is kind of a strange product in that it is a gel that you spray in the way that you would hair spray.

Application:

The directions say to spray a liberal amount on damp or dry hair and style as usual. We didn’t think that worked very well. The gel doesn’t come out evenly like a spray. We found that you got much better hold and coverage if you spray it into your hand and then run evenly through damp hair. Style as usual. You could finish up with a slight spritz afterwards for hold but then again, we don’t think it sprays evenly.

Hold:

It states for control and medium hold. Yes, we got at least a medium hold depending on how much we used. The first time we used it, we used quite a bit not thinking that it would have much of a hold and it gave my sons plastered, hard, crunchy hair. So yes, good hold, and you don’t need that much.

column6: Earthpaste Multi-Flavor Pack
column14:
For this particular 4 pack, it's a great price and variety, but it would be cool to choose your own flavors or have different options.

For the product itself: The packaging is nice looking but not functional. You have to screw the dang cap a zillion times to open or close, and it retains its shape which is annoying when you're at the end of the tube.

The cinnamon flavor has been inconsistent tube to tube, the other flavors are kind of bland and not long lasting or very effective at breath control.

I have to brush much more diligently behind my front teeth to avoid buildup, otherwise I like how my teeth feel with this paste. Have yet to see a dentist since making the switch but my teeth feel pretty good I guess.

I like the minimal ingredients but I feel a little xanthan gum (or something like that?) would help the consistency, since I've found I really have to shake and knead the tubes well before using them to mix the liquids and solids back into a manageable paste. Also, better packaging would help prevent the air pocket fueled explosions that happen pretty often.

column6: Color Oops Hair Color Remover Extra Strength
column13: This stuff worked - thank gawd! *big hair mistake freakout*
column14: I didn't purchase my Oops at Amazon but only because I panicked and ran to the CVS, looked at all the hair paraphernalia, and saw the Color Oops product. I was a little worried but my hair was so dark and as well had a reddish tint that did not look good with my complexion - previously, I had highlighted hair that I'd 8 weeks ago colored a very dark blonde/light brown-that color made my hair more even colored.  Well, my boyfriend wanted to see what I'd look like with my natural dark hair (which is med to dark brown) - so, he picked out the color (my first mistake -laughing!). The med/dark brown I used was a semi-permanent. I applied it yesterday and the results, as I said, were very dark and way too red.  I go into detail like that so can know the state/condition of my hair prior to Oops application in case you have a similar experience to correct.  I applied the Color Opps JUST AS DIRECTED (the only thing I question is that I didn't use the entire bottle and maybe I should have). I put on the hair cap, and let it sit in my hair for the complete 20 minutes. Then the boring part comes: I rinsed it out in the shower, then shampooed and then rinsed for TWENTY MINUTES - no less than that and maybe a minute or two more. While rinsing the 20 min, I would push my fingers/hands through my hair - my hair began to "tangle" pretty bad - I have baby fine hair - but after the 20 minutes, I shampooed again and rinsed for the FIVE MINUTES -no less than that - then I shampooed one more time and rinsed well. I then applied a deep conditioner and worked it through and then combed out the tangles. I rinsed that well, towel-dried, and hoped for the best.  I was pleasantly surprised! The dark color came out; the dark red came out, and what was left is close to where I began after my permanent color faded -- there is still a slight red tint - or golden tint - left to my hair, but the dark brown is gone. I don't know if it took out any of the permanent color from 8 weeks ago - maybe if I'd used more of it it would have, or a second box, which I decided not to do, simply because the color looks kind of pretty - pretty enough - and I want to see what happens over the next few days -- will it fade more? will it darken? I don't want to chance re-coloring it until my hair "rests" for at least a month - unless the color does something weird before then that I need to correct.  After conditioning, I was also surprised at how soft my hair is - and shiny. I checked the drain and my wide-toothed comb (and my detangling wet-hair detangler brush) to see if I was losing any hair, and I did not. My hair feels soft and is in good condition.  I'd use this again if I ever have another color OOPS - which I hope not to repeat. Just remember folks, this stuff does not DEPOSIT color but only takes out color - if you bleached your hair and added color, it'll take it back to bleach (or almost according to how dark or whatever) - if you deposited any kind of color, even dark, there is bleach in there and it will to some degree lift color and then deposit color, so OOPS will take you back to the "lifted" hair color, not to your natural color. If that makes sense.  It does stink somewhat - the odor lingers in the house a little but not my hair - it's not so bad though. Worth it!   Some photos just to show before and after OOPS. While the photo to the left shows hair that doesn't look that bad, it's because you can't see the intense red after the semi-perm color was applied, but believe me, it's there  - the second photo is the after photo and I did it in the light. Lighter!

column13: This one (pomegranate) is the right fit for my type of hair - hair actually looks washed and frankly I was able to go 2-3 days (
column14:
I wanted to try no poo method (with soda and vinegar), but after my husband raised his eyebrows on the idea (which never happens usually), I decided to scale back and use a cleansing conditioner to start. I tried the green one from Renpure too (I think it's mint and smth), but it made my hair a bit greasy.

I have a lot of hair, and it's long but all very thin and have lots of fly aways. This one (pomegranate) is the right fit for my type of hair - hair actually looks washed and frankly I was able to go 2-3 days (for the 1st time in a LOOOONG time) without washing my hair and still felt like my hair was clean. There are a lot of instructions on this one - here are my tips: (1) if you have long hair, you might need more than the recommended 12 pumps (just cover your hair with a very thin layer of this thing) and (2) don't add any as a leave in conditioner (they sat you dan do it, but your hair will look greasy next day - at least if you have thinner hair).

The smell is really pleasant and overall, after couple of washes, it doesn't leave your hair stiff or anything like that.

column6: Dr. Bronner's Pure-Castile Liquid Soap - Baby Unscented, 32oz.
column13: Changed my cleaning habits. Never going back.
column14:
Dr. Bronners is amazing stuff. One bottle of this will last you months. (Maybe weeks if you have an exceptionally large family of cleaning freaks).

When I started down this path, I only used it for refilling my hand soap containers. I dilute it at about 10 parts water 1 part soap - it makes for a very liquidy soap, perfect for the foaming containers which I have since confiscated from friends who still *gasp* buy new things of soap when one goes empty. Before I had the fancy shmancy foaming pumps, I just used the normal soap pumps. It worked fine, but it was runny which took a bit of time to get used to.

But because it is so diluted and still cleans very well, I had a crazy amount of soap on my hands. So I started using it to clean other stuff. Dish detergent was the next thing on the list - I dilute it maybe a touch less than the hand soap (maybe 8 parts water to 1 part soap) and it works equally as well as the name brand dish soap that I used to buy. Only a few times have I felt the need to let things soak a bit longer than I would have otherwise, but even then I tended to soak overnight, so no real change. If you're as crazy as I am, you can add some citrus essential oil to it to help with the degreasing aspects. Just 20 drops or so. It's not necessary though - just gives it a nice scent and I like to think it helps things along a bit. I probably do this about half the time.

Still so much soap left and, well, I ran out of some all purpose spray. Made my own with a bit of Dr. Bronners to a 50/50 mix of water & vinegar. Works AMAZING. I now use Dr. Bronners for just about any cleaning that requires soap. If it's a tough job, I don't dilute it as much. If it's a light job, I dilute it a bit more. If it's something that won't be rinsed (all purpose spray), I dilute it significantly. (Tip on stuff that isn't going to be rinsed, use distilled water if you have really hard water. Otherwise you might feel a bit of film. I just boil some in my electric kettle and let it cool. Works fine.)

Infinitely cheaper, over all, than the stuff you buy in the store. And, bonus: not as many chemicals. I'm not anti chemicals or store bought cleaners, but I've come to the conclusion that they don't work significantly better (if at all), they're more expensive, and they're not any more convenient. It takes all of a minute to fill an old spray/pump/squirt bottle with water, add some Bronners, maybe add some fragrance, and move on. One bottle to do almost all. Never going back.

If you've never used Bronner's in this way, you can easily find loads of tips & suggestions on the Google. Lisa Bronner even has a blog and has posted a chart with dilution rates. And dilution isn't an exact science. You don't have to measure it all out. I just eyeball it.n my electric kettle and let it cool. Works fine.)

column14:
I use, pretty exclusively, only organic and natural face washes, moisturizers, and makeup without harsh chemicals. I have very troublesome oily acne skin. It is miles better than it was before I switched to all natural, but sometimes I need a big gun. This is my big gun when other methods won't work.
I ONLY use this to spot treat. I would NOT recommend using this all over the face. Salicylic acid, the main ingredient, can cause sun sensitivity and irritation of the skin. So use it sparingly!
This has a pleasant fragrance and lasts quite some time. I store it as the photo shows, cap down, and it makes it much easier to dispense the product. Overall, of all the 2% salicylic products, I prefer this one the most.

column13: I Love using this in my anti-aging creams
column14:
I've added Evening Primrose Oil to the home made Shea Butter Cream I make for several years now since discovering how beneficial it is for the skin. I'm very satisfied with this product by Botanical Beauty because it meets the standards I set for the essential oils I use in my skin care products: it's organic, 100% pure, natural, cold pressed, unrefined, cruelty free, and the country of origin is the USA.

Evening Primrose Oil is high in antioxidants, gamma-linolenic acid (GLA), and Omega-6 polyunsaturated fatty acids and other essential fatty acids. Applied topically it helps to moisturize and soften the skin, can rejuvenate tired and aging skin, can make tired eyes look fresher, and is an approved treatment for the alleviation of the symptoms of eczema, and has also been found effective in treating dermatitis in various forms.

Additional Benefits of Topical Application of Evening Primrose Oil:
1. absorbs quickly, won't clog your pores and has no discernible scent
2. good at calming acne flare-ups, while at the same time hydrating skin.
2. regulates the functioning of the oil glands, so it can help dry, combination or oily skin regulate itself and become normal
3. Stimulates circulation and increases oxygenation to tissues so skin cells renew more quickly
4. High concentration of antioxidants to fight free radicals, stimulate collagen production and improve elasticity
5. Several human trials have demonstrated its efficacy in treating inflammation, eczema, pruritus, xerosis, and scaliness
6. Improves hair texture, decreases brittleness, strengthens and nourishes follicles

Potential Negatives:
Typically rare, adverse reactions include headache, nausea, loose stools, and skin rash.

This Organic Evening Primrose Oil by Botanical Beauty comes in a 15ml sized dark amber glass bottle with a medicine dropper top. The dark glass helps protect the oil from being damaged by light, and the dropper makes it easy to measure out the right number of drops you would like to dispense without wasting any. The bottle I received had a use by date of April 2017, so it has a long shelf life is stored in a cool place away from direct sunlight.

column13: Almost as good as the expensive stuff.
column14: I have psoriasis and can only use this product once in awhile.  It tends to product small, itchy spots under my eyes the next day.  I have to thoroughly wash it from my skin and use Elidel to offset the effects.  OTHERWISE:  if you do not have problematic skin, you can use this daily.  It reduced the bags under my eyes to a thin line under the eyelashes.  DO apply with a thin stick (I break off the end of the Q-Tip and use the stick to gently and lightly apply the product).  Apply a thin layer at a time and let it dry completely or the product will flake when you try to add your makeup.  Dry time is about 1.5 minutes per application.  Do not use moisturizers in the area with the serum as it will soften the skin and you will lose the tightening of the skin from the serum.  I would use it every day if it weren't for the fact that I have psoriasis but when I do use it I am most pleased with the results provided I do not over-apply the product or allow it to dry.

column6: Silk'n Blue Acne Solution Device
column14:
I ordered the Silk 'n Blue Acne Solution Device with my fourteen-year-old granddaughter in mind. She is sufferng, like so many young teens, from periodic outbreaks of acne. She and I sat down and opened the box. Inside were the acne device, a cord, a charging device, and a small booklet of instructions in English and a couple of other languages. Both she and I read the instructions. Just inside the front cover is a page of Quick Start Instructions which we both read. The first thing they said to do was plug the charger into the wall and place the device on the charger for 6 to 8 hours. I wouldn't call that a quick start. But we followed the instructions and then went out shopping and had lunch. After we ate, we found a couple of cute summer outfits. That worked to my grand-daughter's advantage. When we got back, she went in and washed her face with plain old soap and water. There was plenty of time for her skin to dry. The charging time was still not up. She and I waited some more. The lesson here is don't expect to be able to use this thing as soon as you open the package. Plan ahead. We didn't.

The 6-hour wait was over and we pressed the on/off switch. A green light flickered to life and finally stayed on. Ready for action. My granddaughter's blemishes were concentrated on her forehead and chin, so those were the areas she concentrated on with the Blue. The LED light was on and she held the Blue against the skin on her forehead for a little over 3 minutes. She found the head of the device was getting pretty warm. She moved the head of the Blue to another place on her forehead every 3 to 4 minutes. She thought the heat was getting pretty warm. She applied the Blue to about 8 areas on her forehead and 3 areas on her chin. It took about 40 minutes to get around to all the areas that had blemishes. She was through for the evening. The Blue was returned to the charger so it would be ready the next morning. After the Blue had been on the charger for another6 hours, I removed it as I had read in the comments not to leave it on after it was fully charged.

The directions said to use the Blue twice a day for 6- to 8-weeks to start and to repeat the treatments twice a week for maintenance. The maintenance schedule seems reasonable but getting there seems to be a real hike to me. Lucky for my granddaughter, it's summer vacation but to keep up that starting schedule during the rest of the year would be difficult.

She managed pretty well through almost 4 weeks of treatments but she was definitely flagging in her enthusiasm. The treatments, lasting at least an half-hour each, twice a day, were taking up an awful lot of time, time she would have preferred doing other things. Fortunately, she was showing some fairly decent results with her skin. Maintenance arrived just in time, or I think she may have given up.

Her skin has been fairly clear now for a couple of weeks and she has been doing the maintenance schedule. I hope she can keep up once school starts again. We discussed the ratings for this device and she felt the amount to time necessary, especially at the beginning, was a real problem. She liked the results aside from the rare new blemish. I thought the time spent charging and getting the Blue off the charger so it didn't overcharge was a pain. All in all, we decided that 3 stars were just about right. The results were pretty good but it took an awful lot of effort to get there.

column13: This caused the worst distress to my complexion that I have ever experienced
column14:
This product presumably interacted with something I got on my face during a dental cleaning. I've been with this dentist and his staff for over two years and no cleaning has ever caused this reaction prior to my use of Neutrogena Rapid Wrinkle Repair Night.
The interaction caused the worst distress to my complexion that I've ever experienced. Raised red patches of thickened skin began to peel the next day and looked absolutely gross. My face remained a fiery red the whole time the skin was peeling off.
I stayed home for four days with this catastrophe and only resolved it by using Bach Flowers skin remedy.
If your skin is sensitive at all, think twice about using this product !!
Neutrogena states on the bottle that it might cause a "mild" reaction.
I'm going to try to get my money back although I threw the box away.

column6: Yes To Blueberries Age Refresh Towelettes
column13: BUYER BEWARE - Company does NOT stand behind its products
column14:
I bought these cleansing towelettes for the convenience of having a product to quickly remove makeup when I don't have time to wash my face after a long day. Unfortunately, these towelettes are VERY heavily perfumed and the scent is just too overwhelming. I found that after using these just a few times that my skin was irritated and I just could not tolerate the very strong scent of these wipes. If you have allergies, are at all sensitive to scented products or have any skin sensitivity issues, I would steer clear of this product. And even after you have finished using the product, the scent actually lingers on your skin and you need to thoroughly wash your face - which defeats the purpose of of the towelette and the need for convenience. Several other reviewers have noted that this was irritating and burned their skin. If your skin is at all sensitive, avoid this product!

I contacted the company to let them know that I experienced a problem with the product and could not use it. My call was routed to some random call center, not even the corporate office, and I was told the company doesn't offer refunds per company policy. I had no way of speaking to someone in the corporate office, only an operator that took down my information. In short, the company DOES NOT STAND BEHIND ITS PRODUCTS. I would not recommend doing business with a company this is so consumer-unfriendly. I refuse to do business with a company that has poor customer service and will not buy any of their products in the future.

For a very good facial cleansing towelette that will not irritate sensitive skin, I recommend Aveeno or Neutrogena. They are mild and non-irritating and not heavily scented.

column14:

column6: Mary Kay Lip Liner, Clear
column13: Didn't work well for me.  Too creamy to do much.
column14: In theory, a clear lip liner should keep lipstick from feathering and bleeding into the fine lines around the mouth.  In execution, however, this Mary Kay lip pencil didn't really do that at all.  It has a very soft consistency, almost creamy, when what is necessary is a waxier formula.  Wax keeps lipstick from wearing off, that's why matte formulas, with a higher wax content, wear longer than creamy, shiny formulas.  So you'd think that the developers of lip pencils would put 2 and 2 together and make a pencil with a high proportion of wax.  Well, Mary Kay certainly didn't do that.  This clear lip pencil wore off pretty quickly (I do lip my lips often though) and didn't keep my lipstick from migrating into the lines and creases around my lips.  Good thing it wasn't expensive.  However, for my next try, I think I'll purchase an Urban Decay 24/7 clear lip liner because they're waterproof and therefore, again in theory, should last longer.  This Mary Kay pencil was not my first foray into clear liner territory, however.  I've tried Revlon, Maybelline and Loreal, all without the astounding success I'd hoped for.  So I'm upping my game and am going to spend more for the UD pencil.  Maybe a waterproof, budgeproof formula is just what I'm looking and hoping for.  I know that the UD 24/7 eye pencils are awesomely wonderful and once dry, don't budge or bleed at all.  I also have two of the 24/7 colored lip pencils and they stand up pretty well but I don't want to carry several different colors around in my purse, hence the "clear" choice.  If you don't have an issue with lipstick wearing off quickly like I do, then this Mary Kay pencil may work for you.  But it certainly doesn't work for me.  I'll just relegate it to the back of my makeup drawer and hopefully find someone to give it to.  It was a total waste of $$$ for me.  I think I'm being quite generous giving it three stars.  It certainly didn't work any better than the drugstore brands I've tried in the past.  The only good thing about it is that it doesn't need to be sharpened.  However, that's not enough of a reason for me to like it.The only good thing about it is that it doesn't need to be sharpened.  However, that's not enough of a reason for me to like it.

column6: Aquaphor Healing Skin Ointment Advanced Therapy, 1.75 oz
column14:
I purchased a six-pack of 1.75-ounce Aquaphor tubes as a lightning deal during December 2014. I didn't know much about Aquaphor at the time. I just knew it was something my doctor had once suggested for my sensitive skin. I saw a good deal on it, and I jumped on it.

I did not realize that Aquaphor is an ointment. I can't stand ointments. I have a collection of prescription ointments that I've stopped using. I didn't like the way they felt on my skin, and honestly, they weren't doing much for me.

Aquaphor is different. It still feels like an ointment, but it actually makes my skin look and feel healthier. My hands are very problematic for me, particularly during the winter. I use Aquaphor like hand lotion at night, but I only use a small amount. After about one week of nightly use, I was amazed at how great my hands looked. They were looking human again! :)

Of course, Aquaphor isn't only for dry, cracked hands. It can be used on feet, chapped lips, minor scrapes, and diaper rash. Just be sure to follow usage instructions!

This is one ointment that I will keep around and will continue to use.

column13: Comparable to the Axe shower tool
column14:
I usually by the Axe brand, because that's what my grocery store carries, and I find this to be comparable. It's only a little big smaller, not enough to bother me, and the rope it hangs from is longer, which is inconsequential from my point of view.

Quality-wise they seem similar. I really don't understand the complaints about the texture - it is supposed to be abrasive. I don't understand the complaints about it being too small or lacking an extra rope, etc. Is it possible these other reviewers misunderstand how to use this too?

As another reviewer who also gave this product 5 stars said, I'm not sure we're all reviewing the same item. I cannot explain the divergence of opinion.

All in all, this is a quite serviceable shower tool for men. It is about the same price as the Axe and accomplishes the same tasks. What more can you ask?

column14:
This gel based sunning lotion is the best I've ever found! It quickly helps give a beautiful golden color hard to achieve unless sun tanning daily. The deep island caramel color is the plus that this item delivers.
The gold flakes look amazing while sunning, and distract from any problem areas yA may have. Once your color has deepened the golden flakes have an amazing shimmer effect, perfect for that after sun evening. The shimmer washes away in the water, beach, shower or pool. If it does get onto your suit or clothing it washes out very easily.
This product is my must have for anytime I'm poolside, on the ocean, or sunning. It's truly amazing how quickly yA will see results. If yA do not have a base tan I'd suggest using caution just to avoid an uncomfortable burn, that will just cause peeling- and yA will loose the desired affect. Once yA have established a base tan - I had no worries and no sunburn! I reapplied as needed, and the cool gel felt amazing on my warm sun kissed skin.

column14: I just began using this product and am very impressed. I returned product to Amazon and reordered; I also wrote feedback to Amazon regarding the reason for return.  The next day I received an e-mail from a rep from TruSkin who apologized for the shortage and asked for an address to send a complimentary bottle to.  They did not need to do that-I was merely offering feedback-but nonetheless I was very impressed with their follow up and customer service.  This, in my opinion, is the way to do business.  Provide a great product such as the Hyaluronic Acid and combine it with class-act customer service...six stars!

column13: This allows me to thicken up what little bit of hair is there and feel better about myself
column14: I am a 30 something year old woman with male pattern baldness. I struggle with this every single day! It affects my self-esteem immensely, I feel as if everyone is staring at me. I think I have even missed out on job opportunities because of it. It is a very real, very hard struggle for me. My hair loss is irreversible, but hopefully controlled. So my only options now are to find ways to live with it. I was excited to try this product. I am thrilled to have been able to! It was a bit discouraging in the beginning because it takes a lot of patience and practice to figure out exactly how to do it. I had a hair stylist friend assist me. I am sure there are videos on how to use it if you don’t have a stylist friend. But stick with it! Figure it out. It has been such a huge relief to be able to go out and not worry that my baldness is showing thru. This allows me to thicken up what little bit of hair is there and feel better about myself. It is not something that you can just wake up, shake in your hair and leave. It does take a bit of time to accomplish good results, but it is worth it! Thank you magikol for helping me get some confidence back! I received this product at a promotional rate in exchange for an honest and unbiased review.

column13: Beautiful Makeup Brush Set!  I have received so many compliments on my makeup since I started using these brushes.
column14:
I am a big makeup fanatic but I always have a hard time finding quality makeup brushes to use.
I was really excited when I saw how beautiful these brushes are and how high quality they are.
They are nice and soft which makes it very easy to apply makeup. The eyeshadow brush blends my shadow beautifully and makes it so easy to get the shadow look.

This set comes in a beautiful leather case with 12 different brushes that are labeled on each one so you know what to use it for. Most makeup brushes I have tried shed like crazy which wasn't fun when it would shed by my eyes. These brushes Don't shed at all and I even tugged on them and nothing came loose which is amazing.

My sister in law is a makeup artist and she was even impressed with these brushes and very jealous.

They are made from premium goat hair and top of the line synthetic bristles but I can't tell which is which because they are all so soft.
My makeup has never looked this great before. I have received so many different compliments on my makeup since I started using these. My friends asked me what expensive makeup I purchased. When in reality i'm still using the same makeup that I have been. So I guess the brush you use makes a huge difference.

I also really love that you can store your makeup brushes in the leather case that they come in. I do clean my brushes after use so they stay looking nice and makeup doesn't get all over the case.

column6: Secret Outlast Clear Gel Antiperspirant and Deodorant Scent, 2.7 Ounce
column14: I'd recently switched deodorants to Secret Clinical Protection, because nothing seemed to work for me in the summer heat. Trouble is, they recommend putting it on at night, and for some reason, it's often difficult for me to remember to put it on before bed! So one morning after I'd forgotten, I decided to try out my Secret Outlast Clear Gel sample, which I got for free to try through BzzAgent. I was honestly expecting to be a sweaty mess, but I totally forgot I was wearing a different deodorant until the end of the day when I thought about how dry I was! The clinical protection is a little stronger, and therefore works a bit better, but I'd say the Outlast Clear Gel definitely works better than other non-clinical deodorants. I also like that the gel doesn't leave white marks on my clothes -- but still be careful, as the gel seems to leave oily-like stains if you get it directly on some fabric. But overall, great product!

column6: Adovia Dead Sea Salt - Pure Dead Sea Bath Salts for Skin Softening Baths and DIY Skin Care Products - Genuine Dead Sea Salts Have More Minerals Than Epsom Salt - Fine Grain
column13: I’ve only used what knowledge I have from using CVS brand epsom salt which is pretty much pouring in the whole thing into the
column14:
After receiving the product as part of a promotion, I had been a little concerned about the packaging since it didn’t have any description that I had read from the promotion and the amazon product page. It makes me think maybe there’s something wrong for why it isn’t being displayed on the bag for the product. However I am aware certain products don’t have to have ingredients listed and such, but if this was on the shelf in a store I probably wouldn’t buy it without that information on there due to my own precaution when buying things that are suppose to help my body health. There’s also no instructions of how to use this product. I know I could use as a scrub to use in the bathtub yet no information of how much I am suppose to apply or pour into it is there. I’ve only used what knowledge I have from using CVS brand epsom salt which is pretty much pouring in the whole thing into the bath tub. The dead sea salt dissolves fairly quickly when I poured it in. The amount of the product can either be seen neutrally with how frequently you’d run out of it. If you use as much as I did(beyond a cup or two of it), then chances are you’ll have about three baths with one bag of this specific quantity of dead sea salt.

Once I had taken my relaxing bath(aka spent two hours napping in the bath), my fiance had surprise he was at my soft skin; I had originally forgotten that dead sea salt could make skin soft. I’m not sure how well it impacted my eczema since it was only a few times I’ve used it unlike the epsom salt experiences I had as a child which would be an every day situation of epsom salt baths. It did smooth those rough patches as far as I noticed but didn’t eliminate it. It would have been awesome if it did but it wasn’t dramatic results. I would rightfully assume if this is better than epsom salt then it should do more impact when it’s used on a daily routine.

I would buy again but probably in a larger quantity since I usequite a large chunk of this product on the first go around. I doubt there are fragranced bath salt made by Adovia but if there was, I’d probably buy that as well once I know it won’t effect my sensitive skin. You can view the attached image for size comparison with my left hand.

column6: St. Ives Timeless Skin Facial Moisturizer, Collagen Elastin 10 oz
column13: For the price, it is a bargain.
column14:
At less than $5 a jar, St. Ives Facial Moisturizer, Timeless Skin Collagen Elastin is quite a bargain. Using it occassionally on my face, nearly daily on my feet and after a month or so I have not hit the bottom of the jar yet.

Be warned that the "light" fragrance is very strong when you initially open the container. I've noticed that the scent has faded (my smell sensitive daughter told me it "doesn't stink so bad" now) as the weeks have passed.

My biggest complaint is that the cream is so slick that it slides off my fingers before I can get it on my skin. Surprisingly, it does not leave an oily residue, the scent quickly fades and even with my sensitive skin and mixing this with magnesium chloride oil does not break out my face, nor anywhere else I put it (feet! this plus mag oil has my feet looking and feeling a couple decades younger!)

Decent product, great price, will probably reorder it as it works great on my feet and hands.

column6: e-voke Scented Soy Wax Massage & Aromatherapy Candle - Minty Koala Natural -Hand Made in the USA Contains Aloe and Vitamin E Oils - Sensual - Leave Skin Soft and Silky Cotton Wicks – Guarantee
column14:
I received a discounted price on this product that I wanted to try for an honest review.
That being said, the candle arrived within the time frame given, in its box, well cushioned with air pockets surrounding it. It was a hot afternoon but no melting occurred.
With just the heat from outside warming the product the candle issued a really strong fragrance & scent throw. It literally scented the downstairs areas of my small townhome.
Lit the following day, it burned cleanly and evenly. Keeping the wick trimmed is a great tip for best candle performance. As this is a strongly scented candle, it will most likely last quite some time. The fragrance is strong to me and a short burn time more than adequately will fragrance a good size area.
The scent is mint with what seems to be a base note of patchouli. For me the patchouli was the most noticeable scent and more permeating. The mint does brighten it to some extent which was good. If you like patchouli blends this would be a great value even at full price due to the extraordinary scent throw & not having to light & use it for long periods to scent your space. Really amazing depth of fragrance in this candle.

column6: Burt's Bees Sensitive Facial Cleansing Towelettes
column13: ... through the whole package and for the most part liked the product
column14:
I've nearly gone through the whole package and for the most part liked the product. I previously used the Neutrogena makeup remover/face wipes from Costco, but decided to try a different product since I was only using that one to finish the massive amount of wipes Costco packaging gives you.. I didn't like how Neutrogena's product made my face feel - felt like an oily residue.

Positives on this product:
- I like how it makes my face feel when I'm done cleaning it with the wipes.
- My face feels clean, refreshed and not oily after use.
- I appreciated that the plastic cover kept the package closed when not in use and didn't cause the wipes to dry out.

Negatives on this product:
- The towelette is not really smooth... it's definitely not rough and touching it with your hands/fingers you can't tell, but when you start to wipe your face you begin to feel it. I think the intent is to gently exfoliate out some of the makeup and dirt, but if you're sensitive to that, not a good thing... for the most part I was ok with it but some days when my face was windburned, it was uncomfortable to wipe my face with these.
- I'm not a fan of the smell of these. Personal preference, but it's just not my thing. I just got the Burt's Bees grapefruit one with the hopes that I will like the scent better.

column6: L'Oréal Paris Super Liner Blackbuster - Black
column14:
This product was very odd. I'm always a fan of liquid eyeliner because it brings forth the crisp black lines we all hope for. This applicator though is kind of horrid, it's pointed and rough and applying the eyeliner takes a learning curve to it. The eyeliner feels wet and sticky like ink and if you hesitant over a part it will continue running. The liner takes very little time to dry but it kind of dries my eyes out. Once it dries, the eyeliner doesn't stay dark and crisp. Instead it looks dried out and grey, you can reapply another line if you want to but it will still come out grey. I solved this by adding another pencil eyeliner over it. This eyeliner does stay all day and does make decent cat eyes as long as you go over it again with a pencil and seal it in. I probably wouldn't purchase this unless I was doing some costume makeup or dramatic makeup that required several products. Not something for my everyday eyeliner usage.

column6: Plus White 5 Minute Bleach Whitening Gel, 3.0 Ounce
column14:
For all those who spent a fortune (like me) on expensive and fancy dentistry whitening solutions that come in syringes or blue light ... this product will amaze you. it's cheap and very effective. I've been using it for more than five years, and swear by it. I use custom-made soft silicone (?) dental trays (price $40 for one pair that will last many years) and one tube of Plus White will last about 4-6 months.

Plus White sometimes comes with a soft blue one-size-fits-all dental tray. It works fine, except that the upper and lower jaw are in one tray so if you are claustrophobic, it is not nice. Instead, try to get two of them and slice them apart with a very sharp knife in the middle to create one upper and one lower tray. Use for up 3-5 days at a time, maximum ten days in a month, for a maximum of 5-10 minutes each time. I use them when I shower. My teeth are really white and healthy. Don't drink coffee or dark liquids for several hours or more after use. Apparently, after whitening, the teeth are more sensitive to staining than otherwise.

And the best of all for me? Don't laugh (like my dentist does ) but being hydrogen peroxide, I find it healthy for my gums. I'm not a dentist or a doctor so I have zero expertise in this field, but after a few days of using this whitening gel, any gum inflammation is gone. This is my experience, and I am not claiming it will have the same effect on you. But I once read that hydrogen peroxide was first used to treat dental disease and it's whitening effect was an unexpected side effect. It makes sense to me, based on my own personal experience.

BYW, I use the Plus White whitening gel as well as the gel toothpaste. So far, it seems to be only available at CVS or online at amazon.

column6: V.T Metallic Tattoos
column14:
These are so fun! I keep seeing metallic tattoos in magazines and everywhere as trendy but hadn't given much thought to them until last week when I saw someone wearing one on their face at the goth club. It was so cool I just had to give them a shot. These are so much fun and gorgeous. There are so many varieties in this pack, I included tons of photos, because I wanted to be certain that you could see them.

They are bright and shiny with clean lines, and so easy to apply. They apply just like the temp tatts I played with as a kid, because they are basically the same thing. Just cut out the one you want, remove the plastic coating, place where you want and put a wet towel over it for 15 or 30 seconds until the paper pulls away cleanly and leaves the image behind. Too easy!
I received these at a discount in exchange for my honest and unbiased review.

column6: Waterpik Water Flosser For Kids, WP-260
column14:
I purchased a WaterPik for my son to use on a recommendation from his dental hygienist. He was about to get braces and she told me that it's imperative to keep your teeth and gums clean during orthodontic treatment. It's important all the time, but discolored teeth can occur if you don't stay on top of it.
This little unit is terrific for several reasons:
Kids are impatient and want to be done cleaning teeth asap. This unit holds enough water to clean for one minute. One and done!
It's small and unobtrusive- easily packed for travel or stowed under a cabinet if needed.
Not too noisy.
Simple as can be to operate.
It's a fu n departure from dental floss- he likes it! Shocking.
I'm kind of jealous and think I may buy one for myself.

column6: Gift of the Magi
column14:
Have been wearing these for months now so I feel like I can write a proper review. I am a huge frankincense and myrrh scent-fan and have struggled for years to find the right scent. No perfume can really get the scent right and I'm wondering if this scent can even be instilled into an alcohol based product. The attar's of course are infused oils so they get the scent just right.

This is my first purchase of attar and I have been very pleased with the products. The scent is present, not too strong but not weak. In previous reviews some write that a single drop is all that is needed but I disagree. For me, one drop was insufficient and I prefer more like 3 or 4. I rub this on my neck and wrists - directly on the skin - NOT on clothing like alcohol based products. The exception to this is I do rub a few drops on a cloth hankie and keep it in my purse. I've found this to be a very nice way to experience the scent, like a soul vacation in one deep breath when I'm stressed.

Overall very pleased with this product and plan to order more. My two jars have lasted a very long time and are definitely worth the price.

I must admit I am not much of a shave gel guy, but I figured to give it a go, why not?

First, the packaging is very nice and bright. I like that the can has a plastic bottom -- no more rusty shaving cream cans by the edge of my sink!
Very easy/clean to dispense -- just a quick turn at the top and you are good to go. Last, but certainly not least, it has a small window on the side so you can see how much is left in the can.

As to the quality of the gel, I found it to be think so you don't need to use a lot to spread all over your face and it lathers up nice and good. The gel had a pleasant and noticeable cooling sensation on my face. At the same time I found the scent to be noticeable but not overpowering, which is the last thing you want. I like to smell good, not that I bathed myself in aftershave, so points to Gillette for getting that balance right!

In terms of how my skin felt post shave, (coupled with my Fusion razor!) this gel gives a very good close shave I found that this gel helped keep my face was moisturized longer than my regular shaving cream.

All in all, I've been shaving with this gel for about 2-3 weeks (I shave about 2-3x a week) and I very much enjoy it. column6: The Natural Dentist Healthy Gums Antigingivitis Mouthwash, Orange Zest, 3 Count
column14: This mouthwash definitely leaves a "refreshed" feeling in my mouth. I like the (orange zest) flavor as well. I dislike mint, so I usually go for mint-free oral products. It tends to irritate my sensitive teeth during the first few seconds of swishing. Also, the directions advise the user to shake vigorously, and when I do that, mouthwash leaks and splashes out everywhere, every time. The cap doesn't seem to have a very tight seal. I can't tell that it's really helped to improve my gum health, as I've very recently enacted other changes to my daily oral regimen. Overall, it's a refreshing wash with a nice flavor. It makes my mouth feel clean, but it does irritate my teeth and my nerves just a bit.

column6: Poppy Austin Pure Argan Oil for Hair & Skin, Organic Finest Grade, 2 fl. oz
column14:
I LOVE this oil! I use it on my skin and hair.

For skin - I put it on every morning after cleansing. It only takes three drops to cover my entire face (one for forehead, two for the rest - gently massaged into the skin), and when I have breakouts or dry spots I'll put an extra drop on my palm and use a finger to gently dab a bit directly onto the blemish/spot (letting it sink in naturally rather than rubbing it in). If there's extra on my hands I simply rub it in as a hand moisturizer. Works fantastic underneath makeup (I like to wait a few minutes to let the skin soak it up before applying makeup) - it makes my concealer blend in incredibly. I repeat the same process after washing my face at night before bed. I use a bit of witch hazel after washing and let it dry before applying the oil; I've found this helps any moisturizer (argan oil included) sink in better/faster.
I had a blister on my finger that had accidentally been peeled off and left a deep gap in the skin - after a week of rubbing one drop of this oil into my hands it was nearly completely healed, not even a trace of a scar left behind.

For hair - I have short hair, about collarbone length, and I rub three drops of oil into my hands and then quickly apply it to my hair (so it doesn't soak too much into my hands - it absorbs pretty fast!), root to tip. Calms any fly-aways or frizzies instantly without making my hair look greasy. I use it only after straightening my hair and it lasts several days until my next wash.

Has a very light scent, I wouldn't know how to describe it, but it doesn't bother me at all and it disappears immediately after application. I'm completely hooked on this stuff; it's the best moisturizer I've ever used!

column6: InstaNatural Eye Gel Cream - Wrinkle, Dark Circle, Fine Line & Redness Reducer - Pure & Organic Anti Aging Blend for Men & Women with Hyaluronic Acid - Fight Bags & Lift Skin Under Eyes – 50ml…
column13: I definitely saw a difference, and it got me to find other great anti-aging products
column14:
I'm always nervous about using face creams under my eyes, the skin is so delicate, so I looked into products specifically for under the eyes. Most of them don't do much, so I didn't expect too much from this. I was pleasantly surprised. It's not a miracle cream, but the skin under my eyes was loose and sagging, and I definitely noticed a difference after using this a couple of weeks. The skin is a firmer and not as puffy. Not a huge difference in the dark circles, but I did notice a change, so that was good as well. After trying this by itself and seeing nice results, I looked into other anti-aging products to improve the rest of my face.

I found a great natural product that gave me even better results on my face. [[ASIN:B00IIPI6CS Bel Essence Intensive Anti Aging Treatment - All-Natural Cream for Erasing Wrinkles. Lift, Firm, Tighten Facial Skin and Fade Fine Lines - 1.5oz]] The rest of my face now matches under my eyes, smooth, and firm, and even better, the lines on my forehead and on my upper lip are almost gone. I got a little daring and tried the bel essence (I figured it would be ok since it was all natural) with the eye gel and wow. The results were even better. The fine lines that were under my eyes are now gone, and the good results from the eye gel got even better - the skin is firmer and my dark circles are even less noticeable (I can tell because I've been using less and less concealer). You have to give the products a little time to work, some people here saw results after a week, took me between 2-3 to start seeing results that made a difference. This is a product I will buy again, with the Bel Essence. Both gave me excellent improvement in the look of my skin, I've taken a few years off my face.
