column6: Philips Norelco S9311/84SP Shaver 9300 - Special Pack
column14:
I've been puting off the review for about 6 months now. The first thing you must know is that if you have never used an electric and this is your first one, you really won't find one much better. First timers must use this for about 4 weeks to train your beard. After that it is pretty close shave all the time. If you have used electric razors before like me, it may take about 3 weeks like it did for me to it shaving well. The trimmer and clippers that come with it are versatile and worth making sure you get them. This comes with the cleaning stand but mine only worked right about one in four tries and often left the razor wet. It also dripped fluid everywhere. It got to the point that I stopped trying to use it and figured it was just a crappy design. Eventually it just kept cycling and I finally called norelco. Turns out I was wrong. The one I got was just defective because they immediately replaced it and even gave me the upgraded version with the timer lights. I've been using it everyday to clean it for about 14 days and it works perfectly. The reason I use the cleaning system everyday is because I found I like to use this razor wet instead of dry. I never really considered it before, but bought the neutrogena sensitive skin shaving cream that uses very little to get the job done. It glides well with the razor and doesn't clog it. Gives me a smooth shave. You can also use regular foams and even just water in the shower. Works well either way. If you prefer to dry shave, be sure to rinse the shaver and heads each time and let them air dry.
Overall this is an excellent razor. It seems expensive but you get what you pay for as far as I'm concerned.

column6: Thayers Alcohol-free Rose Petal Witch Hazel Toner (3 Pack) 12-oz. Bottles
column13: Noticeable Difference in the First Week!
column14:
I actually saw another reviewer who used this religiously before her wedding and she included her entire facial routine and I had to try it! I've been using this for almost 2 weeks. I love it soo much! I have even used it on my kids ant and mosquito bites, and it helped a lot. I love that it's organic ingredients, no alcohol, and non-distilled witch hazel. It smells so. wonderful, I honestly can't be happier with it. My skin has been a wreck since my pregnancies and I have a lot of tiny bumps, blackheads, hormonal flare-ups, and mostly scarring from squeezing which I really shouldn't do but can't help it. Since following this routine I find that my skin is obviously clearing up and it the best it's been in years. Witch Hazel, Rose Petals & Aloe is the perfect combination.

My routine is as follows:

AM:
1) Wash my face with Alba Botanica: Natural Hawaiian Facial Cleanser Pineapple Enzyme
2) Apply Thayers Alcohol-free Rose Petal Witch Hazel with Aloe Vera to dried face with a cotton pad
3) Estée Lauder Clear Difference Advanced Blemish Serum
4) 2 Drops of Desert Essence Organic Jojoba Oil

PM:

1) If I wore makeup I use my regular Neutrogena Rapid Clear Oil-Eliminating Foaming Cleanser to get the mascara and heavy stuff off, and then use a little Shea Moisture African Black Bar Soap on my Olay Pro-X Advanced Cleansing Brush.
2) Apply Thayers Alcohol-free Rose Petal Witch Hazel with Aloe Vera to dried face with a cotton pad
3) Estée Lauder Clear Difference Advanced Blemish Serum
4) 2-3 Drops of Desert Essence Organic Jojoba Oil

column6: Jose Eber 32mm Clipless Curling Iron
column13: Both curling irons are excellent, consistent
column14:
No joke, José Eber Clipless Curling Irons will change your life! I bought my first José Eber 25mm in 2011 and absolutely adore it. I ended up buying the 32mm this past year for fatter curls. Both curling irons are excellent, consistent, and provide shiny, long-lasting curls. I have dark, coarse, thick hair (I'm of Mediterranean descent) and I don't even need to use hairspray with Jose Eber irons and they last until I shower (2-3+ days!). I am not above curling my hair for a wedding, and then not even bothering to properly style my hair the next day and having beach-y waves. So many friends, coworkers, and family have asked about my curls and about 10 have actually just gone out and bought José Eber cliless curling irons.

- The 25mm gives medium-sized curls. I love this size, and find it particularly useful if I'm going to need curly hair all day (i.e., going to a wedding and dancing all night) --- the curls loosen for me so I may start of the day with somewhat tighter ringlets, but depending on humidity, I'll have consistent curls into the night. These curls will last for days, so you can just touch up on days 2 and 3, but you do start with tighter ringlets and may have to loosen slightly.

- The 32mm is great for bouncier, beach-ier waves. The ringlets are somewhat bigger. I tend to use this for work, a dinner or date. For me, this may not work in an extreme humidity situation - I think the curls might fall. If you loosen them, you get a nice Kate Middleton blow-out look. On Day 2 and 3, I do have to touch up much more than the 25mm.

- My girlfriends with blond, fine hair tend to use the 21mm as their hair falls quicker. I personally prefer the 25mm and 32mm for bigger curls.

- Best curling irons I've ever owned and they last a long time - I get compliments all the time! Absolutely changed my life!

column13: want beautiful skin try a mask from my beauty diary for your skin type
column14: Can you say beautiful skin!! Wow I did get the real Beauty Diary brand. I know because of the hologram on the side. I know some people were getting fakes. This seller gives you the real deal. I know my beauty diary masks have been a fave among Asians and now I see why!! This mask is unlike any other mask thst I have tried from the Asian markets. When you pull your mask out there is a plastic cover over the mask itself. You simply line the plastic up smooth it on your face and remove the plastic leaving the mask behind. I must say perfectly in place!! I roller dermed my face before I used this strawberry one. I told my husband well we will see what happens in the morning. I have oily skin. My face breaks out uughh. I am 41 years old. Nobody knows so sshh :-) I woke up to beautiful refreshed skin. I actually stood looking in the mirror smh in amazement. This strawberry one has lactic acid in it Hence the glow. Not a one pimple actually skin was smooth and so soft. Not something I.am used to. I did my roller derm after did this mask for about 40 minutes due to getting my lil angel to bed. I believe this mask is made from rice paper. It's highly saturated. It leaves little essence in the packaging. All the good stuff is soaked in this mask. As I was using it I kept rubbing the essence from the mask into my neck and chest. All I can say is wow and thank you. I am in love with this strawberry mask. I will never be without it. My poor husband lol. Great price on this. You get 10 masks for about 11 dollars. Well worth it!! Thank you Amazon for bringing These wonderful Asian products to the USA for a reasonable price. Thank you to all the Asian women for sharing their make up masks and more with us in the USA. The South Korean products are light years ahead of American brands. I have only Asian beauty products in my arsonal now. Asian companies focus first on great skin then make up. I love Etude house Holika Holika so many more and now my beauty diary masks. I highly recommend this mask for oily skin. All I still can say is Wow!! Make sure when trying any mask that it is for your skin type and issues!! I don't like when I see bad reviews because you didn't research what the mask does for your personal skin type. This is a 20 star product!!

column13: 5 Star Spa Experience in a Bag!
column14:
This is a spa experience in a beautiful, ready-to-gift bag and box. I took the kit with me on a weekend trip to visit my parents, 2 sisters, and their wonderful families. We sat around smelling everything and ooh-ed and aah-ed, commenting on how much it reminds of us of the upscale spas where we went in our single days. We planned to all use this kit and relax, but with 11 kids between us it didn't happen. Time has kept me from using this kit until tonight. I would open the bag, pull out the containers and breathe in the luxurious, pampering smell and hope. Tonight, my husband gave me the gift of time. He took care of everything so I could sink my feet into blissful oblivion. I feet felt so relaxed, and the smell of the soak is A-ma-zing! After a while, I used the soap part of the bar to lather up and the rough part to scrub. It felt really nice too. I didn't want to take my feet out, but was dying of curiosity about the cream. It is SO tingly. It must be the camphor. And moisturizing. I had to put a pair of socks on to walk around the house, so I didn't get anything on the carpet. I feel like I had such a treat tonight. This is the best gift for the woman in your life (or man) that enjoys being pampered, but doesn't get the chance any more. It is literally like bringing the spa home. Great, great gift idea.
I received this item at a discount, in exchange for my honest review. All opinion are completely my own.

column6: NEW Gelish Harmony pH Bond Dehydrator Nail Prep Soak Off Gel Polish 15mL .5oz
column13: Solve the lifting problem unlike regular rubbing alcohol
column14:
I had such a terrible time with lifting every time I did my nails. They wouldn't even make it through a day. I searched and searched online and read someone's review (can't remember where now, perhaps here) that using regular rubbing alcohol didn't work for them either for this step, as others have suggested in order to save money by not purchasing this product. This woman went ahead and purchased this and said the results were amazing and solved her lifting problem somehow so I tried it myself. Yes, it does seem to do the trick. You can see after applying it, how much it dehydrates the nail.
As a tip, I also read that washing your hands with a nail brush and the old-school, blue Dawn dish detergent liquid before starting the Gelish steps really helps with lifting for people with oily nail beds experiencing lifting. I have tried Nail Prep with and without washing with Dawn and I definitely get minimal lifting when washing with Dawn. I experience more lifting if I do not use Dawn, but without the Nail Prep, every nail has lifting. I can't do without this product.

column6: Green Tidings All Natural Deodorant, Extra Strength All Day Protection; 2 Sizes; Unscented or Lavender (Vegan, Certified Cruelty Free)
column13: Best natural deodorant i've found (so far)
column14: Let me tell you, it has been frustrating to find a truly natural deodorant that works great. I discovered Green Tidings online, here on amazon, in my search for an effective product. I gave it a shot due to the very positive, glowing reviews. Well, so glad i did because yes - it works very well! I was & still am very pleased.You're not suppose to apply a lot on, as doing so will be messy (crumbles up and then falls off your pits), plus will stain your shirts. I made the mistake of putting on too much, then working out a good sweat, only to end up staining my clothes! Washing my shirts didn't remove the stains, either. Again, that is due to applying too much. I did get a rash from using it after about a week or two, which lasted for maybe a month - don't remember. It went away and never came back, thankfully. The company does say that one cause of getting a rash is because my skin was being "detoxed" from the garbage of any previous, toxic deodorant. The other reason they said could be a cause, is an allergic reaction to one of the ingrediants. A consistent problem i have with this deodorant, is that it tends to always, once it is low, fall apart. My last one still could have been used for a few weeks, but fell apart onto the floor as i was applying it under my arms. This has happened over and over again, though usually not as soon as it did last time.  Other than using a good (non toxic) deodorant to control odor, i advise eating/drinking lots of organic veggies, plus a few servings of fruit; and sweating out all those toxins. All in all, a good deodorant that works, considering it is truly natural, and not one that claims to be natural... only to contain toxic ingrediants & natural fragrances (such as herban cowboy - just an example from personal use, is all).

column6: Gigi Brazilian Waxing Kit, 14 Ounce
column13: Watch a Youtube Video for help!
column14:
A couple of things first...

1. If you're looking at the pictures of the woman with sticky hands that scare you off like it almost did me, SHE IS DOING IT WRONG.
2. I couldn't have been happier with this purchase!

The photo's and bad reviews scared me at first. I am very new to home waxing and spent some time reading reviews on many different products. Hard wax is known for being less painful which is a big reason I wanted to try it. Let me tell you, I am so happy I did! Watch youtube videos and the video that comes with the kit before trying!

After watching a lot of at home instructional video's I was ready to try it and got the hang of it in no time. No residue on my hands. Slight sticky residue on the area's waxed but that came off really easy with some of the Gigi wax remover. It wasn't very painful except in a few sensitive area's. This kit comes with a variety of applicator sizes which is perfect!

HINT: It sounds silly but use a was strip with this strip less wax! It works perfectly and no mess whatsoever. It even grabs the littlest pieces that may get left behind.

I am now addicted to waxing and the smoothness lasts so long!

column6: AVEENO Active Naturals Soothing Bath Treatment Packets 8 Each
column13: Incredibly soothing for an allergic skin reaction!
column14:
I don't generally have sensitive skin, but after an encounter with a particular body spray, my skin broke out in a rash and hives that worsened over the course of a few days. The medication I was taking to counteract the allergic reaction was slow to work, and I needed more immediate relief. I was too embarrassed of the condition of my skin to leave the house, so I was excited to find this bath treatment available on Prime Now! I ordered it very late at night, along with other Aveeno skin relief products and they were all on my doorstep the next morning.

Soaking for about 30 minutes caused my intense itching to go away immediately. Love this product! It will be my go-to if I ever have any king of itchiness or irritation in the future.

For those worried about clumping, they generally go away if you use very warm water for your bath. If you are really worried about the clumping, or do not desire a hotter bath, combine the contents of the packet with hot water in a cup with a lid and shake it until it's dissolved. Then pour that into your bath.

column6: Odaban Antiperspirant Spray 30 Ml
column13: IT WORKS! Give it a try, you won't be disappointed
column14:
I suffer from excessive sweating and I have never been able to find any product, men or womens, that would lessen my sweating.
Following the directions on the bottle and spraying one squirt on each under arm at night and then washing off in the morning (only once or twice weekly) really does work.
The first week of using this product I kept checking my underarms as I was in disbelief that I wasn't damp. I was able to switch back to women's deodorant and it is effective when I supplement it with Odaban.
This product is also safe to use on other parts of the body, I have also tried it on my feet and the nape of my neck and it is just effective there!
My only advice to anyone about to try this product, DO NOT APPLY TO BROKEN SKIN!!!! The first time I applied it my skin was broke out from using men's deodorant and it burned so bad that I couldn't put my arms down for hours after squirting it onto my underarms. The burning literally brought tears to my eyes, it felt like I had dumped rubbing alcohol on myself!
Final Verdict: This product really works and it is effective at reducing/eliminating perspiration.

column14:
When I was reading about this soap it said your skin will feel different almost immediately after you use it.This soap is very gentle on the skin and a little soap goes a long way. It is a thicker consistency , I usually make sure my face is damp and also wet my finger a little before getting soap out so it is easier. It is very good at taking off make up & suds up nicely. You can feel the coffee grinds exfoliating your skin but it is very gentle. It does have an distinct smell to it but when washing you can’t smell it ( sort of earthy, & only when smelling it out of the jar). As you start rinsing you can really feel the difference in your skin…even on your first wash. My skin felt so soft & smooth. The shea butter in it not only moisturizes but also doesn’t clog up your pores , which is a great combo to have in a face wash. I was shocked how it really did feel different immediately. It tightens & cleans out your pores, giving you nice clean & radiant skin. If you haven’t tried a black soap product yet, I would definitely recommend Desired Diva I’ve Been Carded black facial wash. You won’t be disappointed.

column6: Alpha Hydrox Aha Swipes, 24 Count
column14:
I started using these about 6 months ago, and my life has been a nightmare since..

After a few weeks I started noticing huge pores, and vertical scars all over my face - about 2-3 cm long and 1 cm wide, I can't begin to describe the psychological damage this has done, and the impact it has made to my self esteem.

I never really had much of a skin problem to begin with, mostly black heads on my nose and some sun spots (which is why I used them on my entire face) and I would give anything to have the skin I had then back. I've been on many forums talking to others who have had similar damage, not only from AHA but from Retin-A and other chemicals as well, i've tried writing the company that makes these and asking them if there is anything they can suggest but they won't reply to my email(s). I really do believe the damage this has done to my face is permanent and there is nothing I can do for it now - the best I can do is give you the warning I has I had.

My skin is not exactly scar prone or sensitive either, like most i've suffered from acne but only had one small boxscar before this, please look into these types of products further before deciding to try them - it could very well be the best decision you will ever make, i'm only 26 and i've ruined my skin, it's not too late to save yours.

column6: New Radiance Naturals Vitamin C Serum for Face 20% with Hyaluronic Acid, Organic Aloe + E for Anti-Aging, 1 oz
column14:
Getting old isn't easy! As we get older, the products we use on our skin should change with us. For example, the moisturizer I used in my 20's just won’t cut it for me now! I still need the hydration, but a little anti-aging and wrinkle help would be great too.

This is a great combination product because it offers Vitamin C which helps with collagen levels and also helps reduce wrinkles. It also contains Hyaluronic acid which is great for wrinkles, age & dark spots, and help healing damaged skin.

I like to use this product after I wash my face, but before I use my moisturizer. It helps lock the serum in place, so I can get the benefits all day long. It’s easy to apply, just takes a few seconds to gently rub into your skin.

Immediately I notice less dry skin areas, and over time I’ve noticed a reduction in red areas, fine lines, and even dark spots on my face.

Add in the fact that it contains Vitamin E which is great for your skin’s health, not to mention scars and damaged spots, but also for hydration, healing damaged skin and this product is several individual products rolled into one.

While this won't roll back the years and give you that 20's glow again.. it does help with the dry skin and fine lines.

column6: Herbal Choice Mari Shampoo m/w Organic Green Tea & Peppermint 236ml/ 8oz
column14: I visited this page to buy a second bottle after absolutely loving my first one and thought I'd clear some things up.  As in my headline, I would not call this shampoo. This is soap - natural, eco and animal friendly, herb-infused soap.  I can see why there are bad reviews - the reviewers were expecting shampoo and got soap.  But that's exactly what I want.  I had been searching for a long time to find a natural alternative to shampoo. I quit traditional shampoos and conditioners cold turkey and my natural oils balanced.  I wash my hair with water every day but need a cleaning once every week or two.  I tried DIY alternatives which were a waste of time.  Now I use this as "shampoo" followed by what they call "an ACV rinse" for conditioner (pouring a few teaspoons of apple cider vinegar on your hair, letting it sit for a few minutes, then rinsing it out).  The shampoo smells (and feels) like menthol and the vinegar smells like, well, vinegar.  But after it rinses out, your hair just smells like hair instead of artificial fragrances.  Now my hair is stronger and softer than ever, getting me lots of complements and complaints from the hair dresser when her scissors have trouble cutting it!  So I highly recommend this product to people interested in ditching shampoo for an eco-friendly, hair-improving alternative.  However, if you like your Herbal Essences, you should stick to that.

column6: Tinkle Eyebrow Razor - 12 Pieces
column14: I bought this 12-pack back in May 2015.  At that time, the seller was "beauty international".  That previous purchase linked to this seller, however.  Buyer beware with these things!  I ordered a 3-pack from a different seller a few months prior, and the product was fantastic!  So good that I decided to buy a 12-pack.  When I opened these awhile after receiving, I could immediately see, and feel that they were different.  These counterfeit ones I received have a silver "Tinkle" printed on them, and not well I might add.  The good ones do not.  There are subtle, but visible differences in the design.  The originals have a smooth handle, while the fakes feel a little bit textured.  I recommend to anybody that uses these to beware of the fakes.  Open them right away, and request a return and refund if they're not the originals.  The fakes are of exceptionally poor quality, and don't work well at all.  They mostly just scratch the skin.  The fake is the top one in the photo.

column6: Apex Health & Beauty Premium 6 Piece Blackhead/Blemish Remover Kit with Instructional eBook & Tweezers
column13: My Personal Blackhead and Blemish Buster Kit
column14:
I've struggled with acne my entire life and been to more dermatologists than I can count on one hand. Needless to say- I know how these 'blemish removers' work- because almost all dermatologists use them in cases of severe acne. You find the tool with the correctly sized head (matching the size of the pimple you hope to eliminate). You then use the tool to apply pressure to the area, popping the pimple and immediately cleaning away all of the discharge that comes from it. You use the tool to fully push out all of the discharge from your pimple- which helps cleanse the pore and prevents another pimple from showing up.

So- I got this kit. Instead of paying hundreds of dollars for a doctor to do this to me, I may as well pay the price of the kit and do it myself. Because I'd had this treatment done to me in the past, it was very easy to stand in front of a mirror and do it to myself. When I got a particularly bad break-out (during my period or because of stress), I'd pull this kit out and help nip my zits in the butt before they got too bad. I love this kit because it come in a small zip block case, so I can take it with me when I travel and also have it nicely stored away in my bathroom. I can keep all of the tools in one place, which is very convenient.

The tools are made from stainless steel and are very easy to wash. I run them under very hot water once I'm finished using them, dry them completely, and then set them back in their kit until I need to use them again. I do suggest washing the tools after every use to prevent them from carrying over bacteria and dirt that may cause you to break-out again the next time you use them. Keep them clean and they'll do their job perfectly.

If you struggle with acne, or have a teen who struggles with acne, this kit can be a great investment. You're pretty much avoiding expensive dermatologist appointments and instead opting to face the issue at home. I struggle with adult acne on and off and it's such a relief to have this little handle blackhead and blemish buster tucked away in my bathroom drawer. I use it more than I wish I had to, but I'm glad to have it around when I need it.'s such a relief to have this little handle blackhead and blemish buster tucked away in my bathroom drawer. I use it more than I wish I had to, but I'm glad to have it around when I need it.

column14: I purchased (2) of these - 1 for each of my teenage daughters.  Although they appear to be thin, my daughters say that they are comfortable and, so far, they have been durable. Although not the highest quality, the plastic coating is not that ultra-cheap stuff that cracks easily and feels scratchy so I am pleased. I had researched bath pillows made by other manufacturers before purchasing this item and noticed that a common complaint seem to be that the pillows did not stick well. So,before adhering these to their tubs, I made sure that the tubs were  clean and I then alcohol-swabbed the area to remove any residual oil, etc.that may have been left behind.  Happy to say, these pillows cling well and have not budged an inch.  They are also easy to remove and re-apply when scrubbing out the tub.

column14: This is a must have for the new trend in nail polish. It doesn't alter the matte color and look of matte nail polish. I love the new look. It lasts a long time, all Opi and Zoya nail products. Worth the few extra dollars to have high quality nail polish and top coat to protect your color.

column6: Retseliney Acne Face Wash & Oil Control, Acne Treatment for Face with 2% Salicylic Acid, for Teens, Adult & Hormonal Acne, Clear Blemishes & Acne Scars, Organic Facial Cleanser for Men & Women
column13: A Great Cleanser for Flawless Skin!
column14:
[[VIDEOID:de9541047ea053eff0119e8fbd53e36a]] I suffer from acne occasionally, and it's gotten worse now that I've started working in a greasy kitchen again. This anti-blemish cleanser from Retseliney has really helped keep my skin clear and looking amazing!

My face is very pale and very sensitive, so any harsh ingredients cause me to look red for hours. This cleanser is packed with natural ingredients that are all extremely gentle! The witch hazel in this wash is a known source of salicylic acid, and vitamin c has been shown to gently help reduce signs of aging and help promote skin repair. This cleanser is 100% naturally derived so I know I'm not putting any harmful chemicals onto my skin, and since it's 98% organic I can be comfortable that I'm free from trace chemicals as well!

I'm one that always feels tight after using a strong cleanser, and had kind of accepted it as a fact of life. This great cleanser has made a huge impact on my skin without ever leaving me to feel like my skin's dry or stretched! I love not having to immediately scramble for my moisturizer while still enjoying the same results as if I had used a harsh drugstore brand.

This cleanser (and its mask and moisturizer counterparts, also available) has become my new daily facial cleanser, and I am overjoyed with my results! I was provided with a sample of this cleanser but price doesn't change how effective it is, nor does it effect my review.

column6: MELODYDERM® CAVIAR CREAM - Best Firming & Anti-Age Cream - Rich In Antioxidants - Effectively Reduces Wrinkles & Fine Lines - Deeply Moisturizes & Hydrates the Skin - With Caviar Extract + Collagen + Shea Butter - Gives a Glowing & Radiant skin - Luxurious & Nutritious Skin Care 30g
column14:
I used this product for the past 6 days together with the Melodyderm Gold Serum. I really liked this moisturizer, it is a thicker consistency I find works best for night time application, it absorbs quickly and doesn't leave any greasy residue behind. It has a light scent that stays around for about 2 minutes, I can't really explain it better than it smelling like milk so it's not intrusive or anything. The packaging is in the style of a twist top jar, it is really cute compared to some skincare products who have very generic packaging, this actually looks nice on my counter. I actually prefer not having a pump style container for moisturizer so I don't accidentally take too much and have waste.

This made my skin very supple and healthy looking. After applying it before bed, when I woke up I did have my normal oily mess of a face and I think it's because this helped to balance out my moisture level after cleansing so my face wasn't over producing a bunch at night. The skin around my eyes saw the most improvement with staying nice and plump overnight instead of looking gross and saggy in the morning. I didn't have an issue with any breakouts while using this, nor did I have any blackheads (other than the usual amount.)

I'm including my picture of before and after I started using the caviar cream and gold serum because my skin, while I still have plenty of scars I know, over all looks healthier and even some of my lines have reduced if you look around my mouth and nose area. I'm really happy with my results and these containers should each last me about a month and a half by judging the amount used so far.
For disclosure purposes, I was sent this product for free in exchange for an honest test and review, everything here is of my own personal experiences/knowledge.

column6: Roux Anti-Aging Hair Serum Leave-in Treatment
column13: Ruined my hair and see picture
column14:
I have used your eye lash tint and hair strengthener (this comes in a vial) for over a decade and have been very pleased with those products. My hair was fine texture but it excellent condition on a normal day brushing the residual hair in brush was 8-10.

I used the antiaging serum in the spray bottle and it was a nightmare.

I had just shampooed my hair and combed it out. I applied that serum for the first time and as I was blow drying my hair on the warm setting, not hot, my hair looked like it was fried on the top layer were I had applied this including most of my bangs. It broke off and I had approx 20 to 50 strands of hair each time I ran a comb thru it, prob 4 times and I stopped in fear of messing the already damaged hair up worse.

It is continues to break off despite my using extra conditioning products in my hair including coconut oil, recommended by my hairdresser. It is breaking still more than normal and I have much less hair.I returned the product to Sally's beauty supply and showed them the top layer of my hair and the girl said, Wow...

I added a picture of a hair to demonstrate the damage. The end of the hair shows the most damage along with a many inches until the new grow which is to the far right, prob about 4 inches of new growth. If you enlarge the picture you can visibly see where the damage starts and ends.

column6: Microfiber Hair Towel
column14:
First - size. This hair wrap is slightly smaller than one I bought years ago at Bed, Bath & Beyond. So it almost doesn't fit my average to large head. Maybe it would fit better on a 12-year-old, a person with a small frame, or a person who doesn't have much hair, but it hardly can contain my hair. Hair peeps out around my face, and it easily falls off.

Second - quality. This wrap is thinner than my BBB wrap, and the loop that goes around the button came undone the SECOND time I used it! I had to use a needle and thread to attempt to sew it back on. There wasn't much to "grab" with the thread, but I sewed what I could and it seems to be holding so far.

Third - color. The color is sort of pinky-purple. Not a deep, pretty blue-purple color that I was expecting. Oh, well, it's not a fashion show...

If I were you, I'd look for a better-quality wrap. I certainly will next time.

column6: Crystal Essence Roll-On Deodorants
column14: PROS  +FINALLY an aluminum-free deodorant that actually deodorizes! Shortly after buying this deodorant, I visited my parents in Houston, where it was 102 degrees everyday with 80% humidity. Despite running around sweating all day shopping with my mom and sister, I shockingly did not smell at all. Every aluminum-free deodorant I've tried before this couldn't even do the job with me sitting in an office all day at a computer in a perfect 70 degree room.  +Despite this deodorant being salt based, it did not cause any painful stinging like Soft & Dri Aluminum-Free did for me.  +The scent is pleasant, and you don't really smell it after the first 15 min or so.  CONS  -The only negative is that, like everyone before me mentioned, it goes on really wet and takes a few minutes to dry. It doesn't really matter, though, because it's not like it stains your clothing or anything, like deodorants with aluminum.    update 9/10/15: I take it back! This deodorant gave me a chemical burn on my armpit after about one week of use. Crystal alum NEVER AGAIN

column13: Finally! A flosser that doesn't break between close teeth!
column14:
Sick of using regular floss, I've been looking for a flosser that allowed me to clean between my close teeth for a while now. I've went through four or five different brands and styles and have come up empty until now. Since having my braces taken off 10+ years ago I've had the pleasure of having straight teeth, but that also that makes them extremely difficult to floss.

The flossers I've used in the past all got stuck between my teeth and broke off of the plastic handle. They also shredded as I worked my way through "looser" teeth. The Plackers Twin Line Flosser has finally solved my problem. Not only do I only need one to make it through my whole set of chompers, but to date I have had no shredding and no broken lines. As an added bonus, there is a nice fold out pick to get those pesky food particles that are wedged in there. They also leave a subtle minty taste in your mouth as well, which is nice. I've already ordered more to stock up.

I'm very happy with this purchase, and I'll continue my use of these for quite some time.

column6: Oral SteriClean UV Toothbrush Holder and Sanitizer, FDA Listed Medical Device, Doctor Recommended, Clinically Proven Toothbrush and Multi Electric Head Sanitizer
column13: Trashed it after a couple of months, black mold growth on the inside!
column14:
We liked the idea of using ultraviolet light to sanitize our family toothbrushes, but this thing has a flawed design. The toothbrushes stand upright and the heads face a UV lamp, which may work as advertised. However, the bottom of the brushes goes down into the bottom half of the unit, which is hollow on the inside. I don't know about you, but my toothbrush is wet when I put it in this thing, so inevitably there is moisture pooling in the bottom of the inner chamber.

And, after a few weeks, it bloomed with black mold, growing all around near the handles of our toothbrushes. It might have been possible to crack the thing open and clean it out, but we didn't want a mold farm to host our toothbrushes going forward, and having to clean and disinfect the inside of that thing regularly is not something we're prepared to do.

column14:
I use Oils of Aloha every single night to take off my makeup. I do the oil cleanse method and haven't used soap on my face in years. A couple years ago, I had a horrific breakout caused by a product. The breakout lasted for months and months. Oils of Aloha kukui oil was my only saving grace. After months of constant acne, this helped clear it up fairly quickly. column13: Learn how to use Vitamin A creme correctly
column14: Love this product. All of the bad ratings are coming from people that I don't think have done their research. Remember that side effects of using anything with Vitamin A (Tretoin, Reinova A, Retinol) include, redness, irritation, dryness. When you buy this creme your regime should be wash your face and gently pat dry. Leave for 20 mins. Make sure you face is totally dry as Vitamin A will react with water and cause irritation. Apply a pea sized amount over the face or other treated area. Do not apply too close to the eyes as the creme will naturally migrate. Try not to mix it with moisturiser or put any moisturiser on top. Use it three times a week, at bedtime. Vitamin A is destroyed by sunlight so for maximum benefit use at night. If irritation occurs, ease off the application for until the skin settles, Then try again. Vitamin A cremes are the way forward to fresh, plump complexions, just understand how to use the creme and ease off if you have too much of a reaction. You will see some flaking/peeling but you can gently remove this with a warm clean flannel then apply your normal moisturiser during the day with a sunscreen. Hope this helps people understand the negative reviews some people have posted. And no, I don't sell it. I just swear by it!

column6: Braun CCR4+1 Clean&Renew
column14:
You don't HAVE to use the cleaning function of the Braun. You can use it like any other shaver and clean it with a brush. But if you don't mind paying ~$60/year on these refills, then the cleaning system works great. I hope eventually someone decides to make generic versions of the refills or sells the fluid only so we can refill them (like they do with inkjet printer cartridges). I would NOT take the advice of the guy who recommended using alcohol and lemon juice as a refilling liquid. Lemon has sugar (and other impurities) in it, and alcohol doesn't have lubricating agents and may strip the lubricating that the blades need.

Cleaning every other day may seem like a money-saving idea, but I have found that even if you don't use it for weeks, the cleaning fluid still evaporates and you have to replace it almost as frequently, so I figure I might as well get the benefit of cleaning rather than let the stuff just evaporate away.

I hope Amazon starts selling these things directly since buying it from J&R is not a good deal because of the shipping charges. Instead, go to Walgreens or some other store that sells the shaver system, and buy it there. BestBuy.com sells it for the same price with free shipping. J&R's prices are regular street prices (not 50% off).

If you know the manufacture please tell them the batch of dark star glue is bad.

column13: Great maintenance whitening product without the gum sensivity
column14: I have been extremely impressed with Crest 3D White Brilliance Daily Cleansing System thus far. I received the kit complimentary from BzzAgent and Crest and have been singing its praises since the first day I tried it. The actual toothpaste is gritty yet tasty and makes you feel like it is really deep cleaning. It tastes very similar (if not identical) to Crest 3D White toothpaste (which it actually may be) and I have always found that product enjoyable and efficient. I will admit that for the price, the actual tube of toothpaste, which I tend to use more of, is on the smaller side, but with a sale or a coupon, this would be a great investment. The whitening paste has a bit of a funny, chemical taste to it but I justify it as the whitening power in action. It is comparable to the residue left by the whitening strips of old and it makes me feel like the product is really working. I have sensitive gums and have yet to feel any real sensitivity or pain from using the product. Though only using it a couple days thus far, I am hopeful that I will see some real whitening results moving forward. I can see this as a daily maintenance kit if I can find it on sale! Can't wait to give it a few more weeks of use.

column7: This is the only stuff that truly works for my thick hair, HOWEVER...about 2/3 into using it then wax starts to "ball up" to the point that it looks like you have dandruff.  I've been using this stuff for the last 3+ years and I've only had 1-2 containers where the "balling up" DIDN'T occur.  So, it's great for the first 2/3 of using it, but just know that the last several weeks you're going to look like you have dandruff.  This is some of the more expensive stuff out there, so I would expect for it to be consistent for the whole container, but that's not the case.

column6: Waterproof blue purple black green brown mascara charming longlasting makeup
column13: I do really like it- no clumping - the brush acts like a fine comb- but I do wish it had come sealed.
column14:
I thought I'd try this because good colored mascaras are getting so darn hard to find these days. I meant to order the blue actually, but I got the purple by mistake, but it was my fault and as it turns out, I really like it.

I'm taking a star off because this is NOT sealed in any way. It really needs to be sealed; I'd have felt a lot better about it.
It has a comb style brush, and the first application was very light- it really did not start coloring well until I did about 3 coats, but part of that was just getting the brush primed. Note that the first time you use it- it does get easier once the brush is good and primed.

It does NOT clump, and it doesn't leave fibers everywhere. It feels pretty natural too. Now, my lashes are long, but they are very blonde. This doesn't really thicken lashes, but it does a great job of coloring them, and the colors are bright. I find the purple is very flattering to my light blue eyes. Please ignore my bloodshot eyes in the photo; I had not been up long when I took the picture. The ONLY make up I have on in this picture is THIS mascara, in PURPLE, on one eye. I thought you could see its performance easiest this way. I do not have on any eyeliner. Some of the mascara just got on my lashline. It looked ok so I didn't clean it up.
I'll buy the blue next. :)

column14: Bought the Butterly Shaver pro on July 5th, 2015, & there was supposed to be a free foil body shaver attachment, "while supplies last", but, that did not come with it. I see that is still on the offer, so don't expect it, if that's part of why you're ordering it. Other than that, it works very well, & is very pretty. I like the shape a lot, it's very comfortable to hold, & the way the shavers are angled, combined with the way it angles to where you hold it on your skin makes it glide easily & the shaving of hair quick. No, it doesn't shave as close as a razor, but, who can really expect that? It does very well for what it is, & I like the shape much better than the other straight-edged electric shavers. I would recommend it over other straigh-edged shavers, so if you're thinking of getting one, this one is a good choice.

column6: The Spoiled Mama BalanC pH Toner | Clear Pregnancy Acne
column14: Absolutely love this product! It smells and feels amazing, and it's good to know I'm putting something on my skin that is natural and won't hurt my growing baby in my belly. The only downside of ordering this product is the shipping...I ordered my first bottle and when I picked up the box I noticed it was wet, when I opened it i saw the bottle of product had spilled all over leaving very little in the bottle. I instantly went on Amazon made a return and ordered a new one because I was very excited to try this product out and thought maybe it was a fluke that it opened up in shipping. Well, when I received my second order the product had once again opened up and spilled only a little bit this time but I was still disappointed...being so excited to try the product I just ended up keeping it but I'm still bummed that they don't make sure the lid is tightly screwed on before shipping. Needless to say I'm a little worried to keep ordering from Amazon knowing it will most likely leak during shipping again.  ***update- The Spoiled Mama contacted me directly and told me they would work with Amazon to figure out the shipping problem. They truly have great customer service who care about their customers satisfaction and I hope Amazon can take note on that and fix their shipping practices.

I love the first one I tried, the Crest Pro-Health HD Daily Two-Step Toothpaste System, but this one falls short. So I will stick with my loved Crest brand, just not this product.

The process is simple, brush for one minute with step one. Spit, but don't rinse, and brush for one minute with step 2. Rinse and done.

The problem with this system is in the paste itself. It is gritty and pastey with a fake sugar taste. I understand the theory of the gritty paste is "buff" off stains but I have not noticed any difference in the color of my teeth. Now perhaps that's a good thing, as Crest mentions in their Crest 3D commercials, "If you're not whitening, you're yellowing." but when a product claims to be "99% as white as a professional polish" then I expect better results. column13: it does a pretty good job at ripping them out
column14:
Pros:
-Cheap alternative to an epilator ($17 vs. $60)
-pulls most hairs out
- Convenient/light to carry around in purse, no noise (like an epliator would have)

Cons:
-Time consuming (whilst an epilator can go through fairly quickly, this is much more tedious)
-Does not pull all hairs out, and brakes some (if I'm trying to get one particular hair out - it seems I can't do it - but if I just go in to my peach fuzz, it does a pretty good job at ripping them out. It is definitely not as effective as my epilator.
-Hard to reach areas (neck/bottom of jaw) are very difficult to work on, whereas an eplilator wouldn't have an issue.

I bought this as my epilator died. I'm happy with this as it was cheap. I would not pay more money for this - and I will probably buy an epilator later on.

column6: Cover Mark Leg Magic Very Light 2oz
column13: Amazing for dark circles, but just ok for legs.
column14: I purchased this product as a tattoo cover-up as I was somewhat unhappy with the brand I was using.  (Hint: famous tattoo artist's brand)  I tried this in spite of the mixed reviews and I am fairly happy.  First of all, this product is NOT too light for my legs.  Even though I'm very fair, I have a slight olive tone to my skin, which has made it difficult to find decent body cover-up.  This almost fits the bill except that it's obviously intended for those with a pink hue rather than olive.  I will still use it as it does cover and is much more difficult to smudge than my former brand.  Overall, not too bad for a product that I bought sight unseen.  HOWEVER, I decided to try this for under-eye concealer for my ridiculously dark circles and I was in for a pleasant surprise.  This stuff works wonders, lasts all day and doesn't crease.  I only use a few tiny drops and it covers everything.. I could use the same tube for years and never run out.  MUCH better value than the current expensive eye concealers that I use.  In order to make this look really good under my eyes,  I needed to experiment just a little bit.  I have found that the following steps produce best results: 1) Put a decent moisturizer on.  It should dry a little, but not completely once you apply. 2) Spread a few dots of Cover Mark on your dark circles. 3) The Cover Mark doesn't spread easily as it's thick, so you'll need to work with it a little bit to figure out the best way to spread it. 4) This color will look a bit light on the eyes, so immediately follow with your typical make-up routine, including foundation, to even out the color of  If you do this correctly, you'll look a lot better.  Take a before and after if you are uncertain.  If you don't get it quite right, try again and once you figure out what works best, you'll be really glad you did.  I finally look well-rested after years of dark circles!!  I would give this product 5 enthusiastic stars for eye coverage and 3 to 4 for legs.  It's notreally their fault that the tone is too pink for my legs, but I can't give a glowing leg review if it doesn't work well for me.   EDIT:  I took some pictures of the coverage after a night of insomnia.   In the "after" I still need to add my foundation to balance out the color, but you can see why I was happy with the under eye coverage

column6: COVERGIRL Outlast Stay Luminous Foundation Medium Beige 842, 1 oz
column14:
I often play between my more expensive and drugstore foundations-- day to day I tend to use drugstore finds layered with high end concealer, and for dressier or more hectic days I rely on my more expensive foundations. I have combination/dry skin, and require only lightweight coverage. After receiving Covergirl's Outlast Stay Luminous Foundation for testing I decide to really test its mettle-- so I tried it on during one of my busiest, mid-week, ultra-humid, hot summer days. I was pleasantly surprised-- not only did it hold up even after one very stressful presentation, three meetings and rush-hour insanity, BUT it managed to still give me that "glowing from the inside out" halo effect.

Covergirl's Outlast Stay Luminous Foundation provides natural-looking medium coverage and dries to a slightly dewy finish, but it does NOT add any luminosity or radiance to skin. I also highly suggest using a primer and applying to well moisturized skin if you have normal to dry skin, as I do.
Outlast Stay Luminous Foundation doesn't fade throughout the day, true to its claims. The foundation will emphasize dry patches on skin, fine lines, and any enlarged pores if no primer is used, and if you want that "luminous" effect advertised I had great results by mixing the foundation with my Chanel luminizer.

column6: Loreal Evercurl Conditioner Sulfate-Free 8.5oz Hydracharge
column13: Smells good, but doesn't work well
column14:
I have hair that is half wavy/curly and half slightly wavy/straight, which makes for quite the challenge in both styling and care. I have found products that seem to control my hair adequately, but they are unfortunately quite expensive, so I am always on the quest for different, cheaper, more readily-available products. Unfortunately, my trial of "L'Oreal EverCurl Sulfate-Free Conditioner" was a huge disappointment.

Despite applying a massive amount of conditioner and letting it soak in for several minutes (up to 20 on certain trials!), my hair didn't feel conditioned AT ALL. It wasn't soft, wasn't de-tangled, and was just as frizzy as it was prior to using the conditioner. My curls weren't defined in the least.

Once this conditioner was rinsed out, my hair felt squeaky-clean, which might sound like a good thing, but it felt TOO clean, as if I had only stripped it with a cleanser, and hadn't conditioned it at all.

What this conditioner does have going for it is that it is lightweight (so it doesn't weigh down the hair) and has a very "gentle" fresh scent. I am sensitive to smell, and this conditioner's gentle scent is far from offensive.

I figured out that I could use this conditioner and then use coconut oil for my hair to feel conditioned and de-tangled with defined curls, but the conditioner alone couldn't do that.

column6: Azure Pure Spa Detox Mud Mask with Antioxidant Vitamin C, No Preservatives, Kaolin and Bentonite Clay Ethically Mined in the USA,
column13: Use this mask to achieve an even tone and less oily skin!
column14:
I, personally, have been searching high and low for a mask that doesn't make my skin produce more oil. I have tried many name brands from high end drug stores and even cheap masks. This time, I think I found the one that works best for me - FINALLY!
This is a clay mask - so with that being said, it's not like your traditional mask! It doesn't come wet but instead in a powder form. I had no idea of this and it kinda spilt when I opened it.
Follow the directions when adding water. You seriously don't need more than a 1.5 tsp. A little totally goes a long way! I made too much my first time. I added lavender oil and rose hip oil to mine. I use both for a calming and healing effect. The rose hip oil does wonders for skin
I mixed the product in a plastic cup and with a plastic knife. I then put it on my skin. I always make sure (as with any face mask) to put a decent amount on. If you don't put enough on, you won't get the benefit of the product. I then let it dry and rinsed the rest off in the shower.
Afterwards, my skin was so soft! I could tell my pores had been purged and were no longer clogged. After a few hours, my skin wasn't overly oily like it was trying to compensate with what the mask got rid off. I didn't have any dry flaky spots. My skin tone was SO much more even as well.
My only complaint is that it doesn't last long enough. After two uses, 1/3 of the tub is gone.
I received this product at a discount in exchange for my honest and unbiased review.

column13: Great for skin, not for clothes

I thought that aluminum free deodorants were supposed to stop the yellow stains from showing up, however with this I seem to have even more noticeably yellow stains!? ugh.  As for applying, it behaves exactly like a regular solid stick deodorant (slightly harder to glide on skin). I used to get a few small red bumps which I thought were razor burn, but after using this deodorant by skin is baby smooth. If only I didn't have to worry about the clumps!!

column13: Hannah Natural hair products great for natural hair color.
column14:
This combination of natural herbs is less messy for people like me, who used to henna for several hours, then apply indigo to get black hair. Each is messy and time consuming and henna really needs to be mixed 12 hours in advance. This is at least less time consuming because you're only applying one combo product and doesn't need to be mixed in advance. It also includes some conditioning herbs along with the henna and indigo.
Note: the first time you use this, it might not get to the color you want. You may need several applications. Also find myself using indigo applications in between these, since indigo just doesn't last as long on hair as henna does and you can get a reddish hue after a few weeks. Not a bad look on everybody, but not good on me.
I do mix in a little oil and tea - usually chamomile - just as if I were doing a regular henna application. Learn more about mixing hair recipes at hennapages.com. I use 1 tablespoon of any oil like jojoba, coconut, or even olive oil per 100 grams of powder. I also brew and cool tea to use as the liquid in the mix. Turns out beautifully.

It's really beautiful and perfect for those who enjoy Celtic knots, Claddagh rings and such.

I received the ring a week later (faster than I expected), and finally, after two years of dating, asked her to be my wife on 12/12/15. The ring was far better than anything I expected. This crystal clear diamond on it's beautiful setting are spectacular to look at, and it will make your fiancé feel like a queen from all of the compliments she receives.

It has now been 6 months since purchasing this gorgeous ring, and there have been zero problems with chips, scratches, or lost diamonds. We are getting married on 10/03/15, and I can truly say it is the best decision I have ever made.

column6: JDZ Amulets Tibetan Buddhist 108 Beaded Bracelet Porcelain Prayer Beads Wrist Meditation Mala Bracelet
column13: Beautiful and Fashionable Multicolor Vintage Porcelain Bead Bracelet
column14:
The Tibetan Buddhist Porcelain Prayer Beads Bracelet in Mixed Color by JDZ Amulets is an extremely appealing and attractive accessory that serves to bring out some color into your outfit. You really don’t need to be a Buddhist to wear this. This porcelain bead bracelet was provided for testing and review, and all opinions are my own.

The product comes in a small cute beige and blue canvas draw-string bag. The beads are threaded through with a dark brown elastic cord that stretches for easy accommodation. The ends are tied in an attractive knot with four end beads. Although it’s listed as a bracelet, the string of beads are long enough that you can wear it as a porcelain bead necklace. You can wrap it three or four times around your wrist as a bracelet, depending on your wrist size.

Each porcelain bead is a different color with its own unique patterned speckles. The beads are neither too small nor large and they definitely stand out and make a statement when you have it on. I wore it to work for several days and was immediately accosted by several co-workers who wanted to know where I got my bracelet.

One thing I did notice is that if you have small wrists, you might be able to wrap this arounnd your wrist four times. I have a medium sized wrist and wrapping it three times was too loose for me while four times ended up being too tight. I ended up wearing it higher on my arm for the perfect fit.

column6: 1ct tw Black Diamond Stud Earrings set in .925 Sterling Silver
column14:
There are very few pairs of earrings that I can say I love more than my basic 1.5 inch silver hoops. Something I would wear all the time and pick out to wear every day. These are one of those pairs of earrings. They are simply perfect and oh so beautiful. I wear these with EVERYTHING. They're incredible versatile and can be worn when you are dressed up as well as in you're favorite jeans and tee shirt. To me, they stand out even more than white diamonds. And with white diamonds people never really know if you're wearing real diamonds or if they are simulated stones. Whenever I wear black diamonds, someone always mentions it. They always comment on black diamonds and ask about them.

I've had these in for days, not taking them off once (except just now to take the photo for this review) and they fit very comfortably. I sleep with them in and they don't poke the back of my head at all. No irritation when wearing them either. Also, I have long hair that can sometimes get tangled in jewelry, depending on how smooth (or not) the prongs are that hold stones. My hair hasn't caught in these even once.

The backings on the earring have a nice snug fit, so they aren't loose or fall off at all. But they don't have that ridiculously hard to remove type of backing either. The backings of some studs it so tight that you hurt your ears trying to take your earrings off. These don't have that.

The diamonds themselves are as black as they come. Deep in color and not even the slightest bit of cloudiness in them. The stones are the perfect size too. Large enough to be seen, but not so big they can't be worn as your every day earrings. These are by far my favorite pair of earrings. I love them! '

column6: King Will 8mm Black Tungsten Carbide The Lord's Prayer Polished Finish Wedding Band Ring
column14: My hubs saw a ring similar to this one on Facebook some time ago and decided that this was the one he wanted to replace his wedding band.  I searched several sites that carried this type of ring but Amazon had the best price and the most positive reviews.  After finding it on Amazon it was decided that we would both get new rings and finally have a matching set.  The size is actually true to what we wear unlike the ones I had found on other sites.  Our rings came quicker that we expected and were packaged well, the rings were double boxed.  I was a little worried about any spelling or verse issues since a few people commented that their rings had both issues but they were both perfect!!  My hubs made me wait until he got home from work to even wear mine so he could put it on my finger himself. column13: This is the most perfect faux diamond wedding set I have been able to ...
column14: This is the most perfect faux diamond wedding set I have been able to find. First favorite detail is that is made out of stainless steel and not sterling silver or some other metal that tarnishes and turns colors and your finger colors! Stainless steel is a very durable metal; I have had this set for about 3 weeks now--still looks nice and NO GREEN FINGER! Second favorite detail is that it looks alost exactly like my wedding set which can be found here:http://www.worldjewels.com/antique-1-10-carat-diamond-wedding-set.html. The only difference is the antique detail and the diamond on the outside edges. These are details that are not noticable to most, and can only be seen close up anyhow. I had to have some wedding set to wear at my job, because my wedding set just takes a beating. Just wanted a cheapie to wear for rough days. Third detail I love is, it does not look like one of those oversized, obviously fake sets. It looks very realistic, in fact it is the same size as my real set. It is completely passable as real gold and diamonds ladies!. One final note, I think it runs about 1/2 small. I wear a 6 1/2, I ordered a 7 and fits perfectly! I highly recommend the set for the attributes I named above and a price you can't beat!

I love the glitz and the shiny. Almost every finger is covered with a ring, I usually have one or two necklaces on at any given time, and both ears are pierced twice. But of all the jewelry out there, I have a weakness for cufflinks which is sad because I do not often have an occasion to wear them. Still, I create reasons (I wore them as studs -- instead of studs -- the other day in my 1930s waistcoat) and when I saw these fun initial cufflinks, I wanted them so badly.

They arrived in an attractive black velveteen back with the company logo printed upon it. Inside were the two cufflinks in silver. The link-closures are extremely easy to manipulate and once you put them in your shirt cuff, they stay put. They don't tarnish and they're very durable. I've also had a number of my friends ask me about them, wanting their own initials on their own set of cufflinks. Apparently, they make me look sophisticated (their words)! I'm very happy with them!

column13: Very pretty for someone with the \right\" skin and hair tones"
column14:
As the patriarch of a large family -- 100 plus and counting -- these are very pretty and in the fullness of Vine time, will make an excellent gift -- someone will get dibs on them at a family reunion in the fall.

Note: these require pierced ears to be worn, obvious to many, but frankly wasn't to me.

Delicate, very pretty, 18k gold plating really makes a difference over 16k or 14k -- look for yourself at your next craft fair.

The brown color is a bit problematic -- the color on Amazon is close to true, but they will not go with everyone's hair or skin coloring -- order with care.

Personally, I think a different color -- blue or red or even yellow would show better with the delicacy of the design. But, everyone's mileage will vary, and with the right skin and hair tones, these can be stunning.

Robert C. Ross
August 2015

column14:
This was received for free or at a discount in hopes of an honest review. All thoughts are my own and no other's. This review is in the guidelines of the FTC.

If anyone was wondering on the ring, if the purple is visible, not very much. I think it would work great for a wedding band, engagement ring, promise ring or even just as a gift. The Tungsten is a great and highly recommended metal for jewelry. It's really a very sturdy material and has loads of quality benefits to it. It's shiny and polishes well. It's easy to clean via toothpaste and toothbrush. I've always been one for a strange and yet different wedding ring. Mine is camo and silver. I love that because I'm a camo girl all the way. I have to highly recommend this ring to anyone that wants something that is of high quality at an affordable price for a wedding band.

column6: King Will Men's 8mm Black Tungsten with Crisscross Pattern Single Cz Cubic Zirconia Ring
column14: I really really liked this ring. My husband already has a black tungsten ring that he wears as a wedding band and I liked the way this one looked so decided to get it for him to be able to trade out. I have a bit of a selfish reason also though because honestly a black wedding band stands out and will definitely be noticed by all around :) The ring is a very nice ring, it has the perfect shine to it and yet still looks very masculine. Also from a womans perspective the criss cross pattern catches the light very nicely and causes a nice reflection of light. The Cz is a very small stone that adds to the masculinity of the ring but I thought also added to being able to wear it as a wedding band. The ring fits comfortably and the inside is smooth and slightly rounded adding to the comfort. It does have a bit of weight to it but after some time of wearing it is no longer noticed. Overall a very very nice ring especially for the price. **This product was received at a discounted price in exchange for my honest review.

column13: Wonderful Earrings and Good Layering Necklace
column14:
Buy it for the earrings and for a layering necklace.
The earrings:
1) An excellent length
2) Beautiful. I absolutely love them.
3) 5 stars for the earrings.

The necklace:
1) Maybe my set was messed up, but the pendant was the same length as the earrings. I measured. 2.6 cm or an inch. So it looks small. Not like the pictures.
2) Design flaw. One of the other reviewers said hers didn't lay flat. Mine lays mostly flat, but the top pearl always leans left.
3) All in all, at this point I'd give it 2 stars for the necklace, but it layers well so 3 stars. I put it on one of the shortest settings and paired it with a longer necklace. I happened to have a longer necklace in gold, with a V shape like this one, with a few pearls on it. I got lucky. Just getting a second one of these necklaces and adding a 2-3" extender to the end of it may work nicely as well. Especially if at least one of the pendants is smaller than the page says like mine was. Good luck.

Rose Gold Plated Sterling Silver Pink and White Cubic Zirconia Penguin Pendant Necklace (0.33 cttw), 18\" Jewelry 5 0 0 Y N Great little piece, especially for the price I've bought penguin-themed jewelry from Amazon before, including the [[ASIN:B006TSP8FO Sterling Silver Black and White Diamond Penguin Pendant Necklace, 18\\\"]], and honestly, I think I like this little guy better.

First off, the chain is basically a throwaway. It's the default thin-as-string chain that comes with most necklaces these days. If you're even a little rough with your jewelry, you'll want to replace this with a sturdier chain as soon as possible. The only gotcha is that the hole that you thread the chain through is somewhat on the thin side, so you probably won't get anything like a wheat chain or herringbone through it (unless it is also on the thin side). You could always add a jump ring, but that'd probably cause the pendant to twist wrong.

The shape is on the subtle side I think. Unless someone really took time to look at it, at first glance, someone would probably think it's a leaf or something along those lines. The rose gold plating is also on the subtle side, and blends with the base silver well. The cubic zirconia stones are on the small side, but when exposed to direct light, they shine very nicely and produce quite a few rainbow highlights.

Size-wise, I think it's a good balance between being large enough to see detail, but small enough that it doesn't look like costume jewelry. If you split a nickel in half, you get the approximate size of this pendant.

For the price point, I think this little guy is a great purchase. A nice necklace for the penguin lover in your life."

18k Gold and Rhodium Plated Sterling Silver Two Tone Diamond Love Knot Pendant Necklace (1/10cttw, I-J Color, I2-I3 Clarity), 18\" Jewelry 4 0 0 Y N Interesting and eye catching As with other offerings from the Amazon Collection, I found this to be an interesting and eye-catching piece.

The pendant is not overdone or overly flashy. The front makes it look as though it's kind of a ball (if that makes sense), but when you turn it over you see that it's a façade. This does have the net effect of making the pendant lighter, but frankly...if it flips over while wearing it, it's going to look a bit odd. So I guess what I'm trying to say is that there's a definite front and back to this pendant.

The chain has nice fine links to it and gives off an elegantly feminine impression.

Now then - the diamonds. Yes, there are some in here. And yes, at 1/10 cttw you can barely see them. I do have to kind of wonder why a color/clarity code is given, because at the size of these stones it's not like it matters much. Suffice it to say that while the stones add some very interesting glitter to the pendant, it's not like they are huge.

As an accent or everyday piece of jewelry, this excels. I think it looks rather nice and adds a little touch of elegance to most ensembles. 2015-08-06 US 14678958 R2UURXCBZ478ZQ B00KR9ZZ9U 586332230 Sterling Silver Swarovski Clear Crystal Dangle Earrings Jewelry 5 0 0 N Y I love them! I shoot a lot of on site photo sessions, typically dark themed, in abandoned buildings and Anime cosplay. This bracelet is the perfect addition to my accessory kit. Biker, death, goth and more.

The quality of this piece is excellent. I have the 8.5" one and have a medium wrist - it's a *little* loose, so definitely measure your wrist. It's 8.5" from tip to tip. It's not lightweight, weighing 4.6 ounces - it looks and feels substantial. Each skull is .3/4"x1/2" - the clasp is the same size.

The clasp is engraved with "Stainless Steel 316L" - this is "jewelry grade" stainless that won't pit or turn black.

This is a really nice bracelet - nothing negative to say about it - and I always look for the negatives.

column6: Pink SWAROVSKI ELEMENTS Crystal Teddy Bear Charm Pendant Necklace Women Fashion Animal Jewelry
column13: When the sun catches it be prepared to be blinded by a rainbow of sparkling light
column14:
I wondered if this bear was going to be as big as it appeared online. Oh yes, it most certainly is. The bear his HUGE and covered in gorgeous colorful crystals. It's so large that rather than using it as a necklace my daughter is using it as a sun-catcher in her window. When the sunshine hits this bear it's like an explosion of rainbow sparkling light. So pretty!

And they didn't put a wimpy chain on this necklace either. The bear has some weight, so they provided a thick chain that is made to comfortably support the bear's size. The chain is nice an long too. Which is because if you are planning on wearing this as a pendant, it's not one to be worn up around your neck.

If you love BIG glittery stunning statement making pendants, this one is for you. Even the little arms and legs are jointed, so the bear has some moment. It's not a stiff metal bear. It's more like wearing a little bendable teddy bear covered in rainbow crystal. The arms have more movement than the legs do. The only thing that would make this bear even cuter was if the legs could bend all the way up like the arms can. Then you could sit the bear down somewhere and it would sit up on it's own. But the legs don't adjust quite that far. But the movement in the legs and arms is just a bonus. This necklace is amazing either way. And be ready to be blinded when the mid-day sunshine catches it!

Sample provided for review

US	49214860	R3178Q9U6JVKTI	B0016L5A9S	84700284	18k Yellow Gold Plated Sterling Silver Tiger Eye Dangle Earrings	Jewelry	3	1	2	Y	N	\"At a flea market I always head for the junk jewelry table first.\"--Ethel Merman"
column7:
Sad to say, Ethel probably would have liked these earrings. My main problem with these Gold Plated Dangles from the Amazon collection is the asking price. The full list price is $179.99--and that is an absurdity. No jewelry store would get that for these earrings. They look like something I might find at Nordstrom Rack for twenty bucks. They are described as "lightweight"; that is because they are "flimsy". The best aspect of the set is the small tiger's eye above each hoop. It is lovely and polished to perfection.

I am giving this set three stars only because my parents thought they were beautiful. Personally, I think most of the pieces in the Amazon Curated Collection are rather tired from a design aspect, but I did expect to like these earrings. Until I got the package, opened the black box with a "Made in China" sticker on the front, and got a look at the actual product. Not even worth the steeply discounted current price of just under forty dollars and rating:

GRADE: C
The earrings come with no informational insert about them or the collection. Nada. Just the "Made in China" sticker. Well it certainly is "imported", as stated on the website.

column6: 18k Gold and Rhodium Plated Sterling Silver Two Tone Diamond Open Dangle Earrings (1/10cttw, I-J Color, I2-I3 Clarity)
column14: I received these earrings and they are exactly as pictured. I wear a lot of mixed metals (yellow gold, silver, white gold, rose gold) and these go with everything. I have long hair and these look terrific and don't get lost in it. They're not huge or heavy but they're 'hip'. The wires on them are LONG, in my opinion, and they come with a plastic slide back (not pictured) so you can secure them where you want them. (I tried it low and found I prefer it higher and closer to my lobe so they don't slip but it's a personal choice) I didn't find them slipping forward or falling out, which was nice, but I would not use them without the back to be sure. These earrings have movement, which makes them more hip and youthful than, say, traditional hoops or solitaires. (With my long hair this was a plus.). I can have issues with metal and these earrings did not leave a mark or irritate my ears. The diamonds are nice-they are a pave and set in the silver with a setting to maximize their dazzle-but they're not Breakfast at Tiffany's glam. I know online can be deceiving and these make the most of the setting they use. The sparkle makes them very flattering, especially near the face. Highly suggest these as a gift because of broad appeal.

column13: Was looking for inexpensive but fun earrings, knowing full well what inexpensive means for ...
column14: Was looking for inexpensive but fun earrings, knowing full well what inexpensive means for quality. These surpass the poor quality meter by a mile. They arrived in several pieces, almost like the assembler threw them into the shipping bag without so much as even trying to put them together. Jewelry making is a part time hobby for me so fixing them upon arrival was simple. The part that annoyed me the most is they constantly fell apart, almost every time I picked them up. I finally invested about 1/2 hour of my time tightening, cinching and closing gapped rings and prongs and centering crooked stones. Also, at some point I will have to invest in at least another 1/2 hour cutting and shaving down prongs that stick out @ 1/8" past the stones. While nowhere near as annoying as the falling apart issue, it is still quite noticeable but fixable.  These are $5-$8 earring at BEST and if you are willing to take a little time, worth that. Otherwise find a friend that makes jewelry and give them the $20, send them to Michaels and have them make these for you.

column13: I'm a little skeptical as to whether or not they're actually 1G or not due to the fact that they went in my ears so easily.. How
column14:
Came in a week earlier than estimated delivery date. I'm a little skeptical as to whether or not they're actually 1G or not due to the fact that they went in my ears so easily.. However I'll do an update when I stretch up to 0G. Great plugs.

**UPDATE**
I kept the 1G plugs in for about a week or so until I stretched up to 0G. (I'm overall an impatient person so I couldn't go longer than a week sadly) However I noticed that my left ear lobe was larger in diameter than before and the 0G taper went in smoothly. The plug definitely helped with that stretch. Unfortunately my right ear lobe was still stubborn, but after some time I got the taper through and I'm now at a 0G for both ears. So in conclusion, these plugs do make reaching 0G just a bit easier.
